title: nana's christmas bread
directions: Heat milk almost to boiling.
Stir in sugar, butter and salt. Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and stir in 3 cups of flour.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Add cardamon and eggs to mixture.
Mix candied fruit and raisins with 1/4 cup flour and add to dough.
Add just enough flour to make soft dough that's not sticky (about 1 cup).
Knead on well floured board, about 6 minutes.
Cover and let rise until light, about 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Punch down dough and divide in half and place in loaf pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 50 minutes or until brown.
Combine powdered sugar and milk; mix well and drizzle over cooled bread.

title: chow mein noodle chicken
directions: Mix soup and mix well.
Put chicken on bottom of Pyrex oblong dish and then add soup mixture.
Put chow mein noodles on top. Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: gingerbread sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg.
Add to boiling water.
Cook slowly.
Add lemon juice and raisins.

title: chocolate cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt well.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Blend flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt together in another bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in air tight container.
Use 1/4 c. in 8 oz. coffee mug.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Cut fillets in about 1-inch cubes.
Fry bacon until crisp and browned.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Add water and potatoes; cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are partially tender.
Add fish and cook until it can be flaked easily when tested with a fork. Add milk and seasonings; heat.
Serve immediately with chopped parsley sprinkled over the top.
Serves 6.

title: baking powder sopaipillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add water and mix well working dough until smooth.
Cover; let stand 20 minutes. Preheat about 2 inches vegetable oil to 420° in an electric skillet.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured board.
Cut into 3 to 4 inch squares and fry until golden on both sides, turning once.
If the fat isn't hot enough the sopaipillas will puff and become hollow shortly after adding to fat.
Drain sopaipillas.
May be dusted with a sugar cinnamon mixture and served as a dessert with New Mexican chocolate or may be stuffed. Suggestions:
Good with pinto beans, green chilies, onions and tomatoes (chopped) or honey.
Yields 4 dozen medium sopaipillas.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and milk; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 1 to 2 minutes or until sugar dissolves (I use a blender).
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a baking pan. Pour boiling water in baking pan to depth of 1-inch. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yields 6 servings.

title: giant chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. In large bowl, combine sugars, butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: jean's cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Put in a greased spring pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 10 minutes. Turn off heat and leave in oven for 2 more hours.
This cake is better after being refrigerated overnight.
Can be made with no or low-fat cheese and Egg Beaters.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soup, in order listed; mix well. Form into large patties and roll in flour. Brown on both sides in butter.
Pour soup with 1 can of water over meat patties and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sesame shrimp
directions: Brown seeds lightly in oil.
Remove.
Add to pan the onions, soy sauce and salt.
Cook briefly.
Add asparagus and shrimp. Simmer just until cooked.
Add seed.
Serve over 3 cups rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix with mixer until well blended, then put in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground round in skillet and drain off fat.
Add bacon and onions; simmer.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; mix well.
Cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then cook, without stirring, to 250°.

Remove from heat and pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream, into the beaten egg whites. Add vanilla and continue beating until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull. Fold in nuts. Spread quickly onto waxed paper or a buttered pan. Cut into squares when firm.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed butter, sugar and eggs. Beat well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla and water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with your favorite fudge frosting or German chocolate frosting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, melted margarine, eggs, bananas and nuts.
Mix thoroughly on medium speed.
Pour into 2 well-greased and waxed paper lined loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the middle comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Mix with green pepper, celery, onion, carrot, celery seed and pimento and combine with sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Let salad sit in refrigerator at least 24 hours.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: ham casserole
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper.
Brown in oil.
Add ham and saute. Add soup and milk.
Mix well. Put into casserole dish.
Cover with biscuits (canned or homemade).
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: luncheon casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients together, except almonds and cornflakes.
Spread almonds on top.
Then spread cornflakes on top of almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar gradually, beating until mixture thickens.
Add flour; beat until blended and add remaining ingredients.
Put into freezer and fill to line with whole milk. Makes 5 quarts.

title: seafood pasta
directions: In medium skillet saute scallops and hot butter 2 to 3 minutes until opaque.
Place in large bowl with lemon juice, salt, pepper, crabmeat, tomatoes, basil leaves, Parmesan cheese, olive oil, cayenne pepper and garlic.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
After 45 minutes prepare linguine according to package directions.
Drain and toss immediately with seafood mixture.
Place on serving plate.
Garnish with basil sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together syrup, sugar, peanuts and salt.
Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla to the syrup mixture. Blend well.
Microwave on High for 1 minute longer.
Add the soda and lightly stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto a sheet of aluminum foil.
Let cool for 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except won ton skins.
Fill skins, seal and deep fry.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet; saute shallots and crawfish tails.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes on low heat, stirring constantly. Add half and half and seasoning.
Boil fettuccine in separate pot.
Add salt to water.
Drain.
Add to crawfish tails and sauce. Simmer over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter chicken
directions: In small bowl, blend together egg, peanut butter, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Dip chicken in flour, then in peanut butter mixture.

title: no-frills fish dish
directions: In a shallow greased pan, place fish.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes easily, 15 to 20 minutes, depending on thickness of fish.

title: party bread pudding
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Slowly add soda and milk.
Heat to blend.
Add bread cubes, salt and vanilla.
Beat eggs; add eggs to bread mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
To prevent curdling, place baking dish in cake pan or any container of hot water.
Can add raisins if you wish.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil. Remove from heat and place tea bags in water. Cover and let steep 6 minutes; remove bags. Tie spices in cheesecloth or place in spice bag and add to tea. Leave to steep 30 minutes and then remove spices. Add the Jell-O and juices and stir well. Will keep well in refrigerator. Heat to serve.

title: lively pink punch
directions: Mix juices and keep in cold place.
Add scoops of raspberry sherbet and ginger ale 5 minutes before serving.
Yield: 30 servings.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on package.
As it thickens, stir in the dry cake mix.
Continue stirring until fairly smooth.
It will be slightly lumpy.	Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with butterscotch morsels.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meat balls in hot vegetable oil until brown. Place in baking dish.
Combine rest in medium saucepan.
Boil. Cook over low heat one minute.
Stir.
Pour sauce over meat balls. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in large saucepan according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
about 4 cups.

title: eggless-milkless-butterless cake
directions: Boil all together for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add 1 teaspoon soda, dissolved in a little water.
Add sifted together 2 cups flour and 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(One batch equals a bread size loaf.)

title: new potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and place into a casserole dish.
Crumble bacon on
top
of
potatoes
and
sprinkle with cheese.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mushrooms with sweet cream
directions: Cook mushrooms until tender; add margarine until melted.
Add flour with about 2 tablespoons of water slowly until mushrooms thicken.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg and buttermilk. Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix only until all is moist.

title: coffee meringue torte
directions: Beat egg whites in a bowl until foamy.
Add cream of tartar. Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Beat for 2 more minutes. Cut four 8-inch circles from parchment.
Pipe meringue into 4 equal circles; spread evenly with spatula.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool.
Remove parchment.
Spread coffee butter cream between layers.
Garnish top and side with whipped cream and dusting of cocoa over top. Serve within 2 hours.
Serves 16.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. Blend sugar and flour in heavy pan. Add eggs, butter and pineapple. Cook on low until thick. Remove from heat. Add coconut. Put on warm cake.

title: friendship bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with 2 inches water; add salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain, rinse and add 2 quarts water and ham or ham hocks.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly 3 hours.
(Or, wash beans and slowly drop into 2 quarts of boiling water so that the water does not stop boiling; reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.)

title: orange nut bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg.
Add milk and sweetener.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until all flour is moistened, then gradually stir in melted butter or margarine.
Fold in fruit spread and nuts, mixing as little as possible.
Transfer to lightly greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes, or until loaf springs back when pressed lightly with finger.
Cool before slicing.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: orange blossom cake
directions: Measure the first 3 ingredients into sifter.
Measure the next 5 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Measure the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar into another mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients over oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar with beater until mixture stands in very stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites thoroughly into batter.
Do not stir or beat.
Bake in an ungreased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes (glass dish at 325° for 30 minutes). Remove from oven.
Cool by turning pan upside down.
(I put a spice can on each corner to hold it up so it doesn't touch the cupboard.) To remove, run knife around the edge and loosen.
Split cake in two layers and spread whipped cream between layers and top.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with orange sections, if desired.

title: chicken and mushroom crepes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in 2 tablespoons butter, cook mushrooms; remove to bowl.
In same pan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
In bowl, mix broth, sherry, yolks and 1 cup milk.
Stir into flour mixture; cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese.

title: molded carrot salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package.
Add all chopped ingredients and pour in individual molds.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bacon wrapped oysters
directions: Wrap bacon halves around oysters.
Secure with toothpick. Arrange in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Place in 325° oven and bake, watching carefully.
Drain off liquid and place back in oven and turn on broil.
Broil to get bacon crisp but not burnt. Serve warm.

title: vegetable kebabs
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Bake in shallow, greased pan at 425° for 20 minutes or until center is dry and top is golden brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fill churn container; finish filling with milk.
Churn.

title: mounds bar
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and wax, and pat into two 9 x 12-inch pans.
Freeze 2 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Melt chips and wax.
Cut into small bars and dip in chocolate.

title: quickie rolls(serving size: 12)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes a dozen.

title: pancit canton(filipino chow-mein)
directions: Saute garlic in cooking oil.
Add onion until brown.
Mix cooked pork and season with soy sauce, salt and m.s.g. and simmer for a short while.
Add carrot and pork broth to meat.
Let boil. Rinse canton noodle and mix in boiling broth.
Keep stirring over low fire until noodle is cooked.
Serve hot and garnish with eggs, sausage and green onions.
If desired, lemon can be squeezed over the pancit for more flavor.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix with water and oil.
Add eggs, poppy seed and almond extract.
Bake in a round tubular cake pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 40 minutes. Dribble with a small amount of powdered sugar frosting.

title: canadian honey drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Roll teaspoons of dough in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Very good with apricot or strawberry jam.

title: punch
directions: Mix water and sugar and boil, then mix all the ingredients, except Sprite or ginger ale, and freeze overnight.	Add Sprite or ginger ale just before serving.

title: marinated fresh tomatoes
directions: Combine ingredients; put into a tightly covered dish. Refrigerate and serve.

title: ashley wilson's quick pie pastry
directions: Using steel knife blade, place all ingredients, except water, in work bowl of food processor.
Process 5 to 10 seconds or until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With machine running, pour ice water slowly, 1 tablespoon at a time, through feed tube.
Stop processor as soon as dough forms ball.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter. Mix all ingredients together; let sit overnight in refrigerator. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven. Enjoy.

title: candied chicken wings
directions: Cut wing tips off and discard.
Cut remaining pieces into two parts.
Place wings on foil lined cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine soy sauce, brown sugar and catsup.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in a single layer in frypan or baking dish.
Cover with tomato soup which has been diluted with 1/2 cup water, then the peas.
Cover the dish and bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add more water when necessary.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Stir in sugar and blend.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; brown meat.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients except flour and milk. Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining milk and heat, stirring frequently.
Do not boil after adding remaining milk.
This makes quite a large amount.

title: macaroni salad
directions: After cooking macaroni, drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Put into fridge to cool off.
Transfer macaroni to large bowl and stir in desired amount of mayo & mustard.
Stir in diced hard boiled eggs and olives.
Next, sprinkle desired amount of garlic powder,
onion salt & ground pepper.
Stir well and sprinkle with paprika.

title: vegetable combo
directions: Pour dressing over combined beans and tomatoes.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours.
Just before serving, add mushrooms and cheese.
Toss lightly.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients and pour over bread cubes in a baking dish.
Add enough milk to fill casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
For added variations a few drops of almond extract can be added for a different flavor.
Fat free sour cream and low or no sugar pudding works well too.
A little cinnamon sprinkled on top is optional.
Arrange fruits of choice on platter with dip in middle.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time. Add vanilla, powdered sugar, salt and flour.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in powdered sugar on one side.
Shape in balls. Place on greased sheet the side down without sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350 degree oven for about 35 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain in sieve, pressing out as much moisture as possible with back of spoon.
In medium bowl, combine spinach, stuffing mix, Parmesan cheese, eggs, butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly and roll in balls the size of large marbles, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
After balls are completely frozen, remove and store in plastic bag in freezer.

title: quick spoon bread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour margarine and corn into casserole.
Blend in sour cream.
Beat eggs and stir into casserole along with corn muffin mix.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter, vanilla and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs, then add peanut butter, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Shape into 2-inch cookies and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: orange pineapple filling
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Spread on your favorite cake.
Enough for 3 or 4 layers.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg all together. Cream shortening, add brown sugar and cream together.

Add eggs, sour cream, and put nuts in the mix or on top of the cookies. Add flour. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour and drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. After cookies are cool, ice with icing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Drain and mash squash. Drain again after mashing if needed.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease 2-quart dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes until well done.
Drain well.
Cream egg, butter, sugar and flour.
Mix with potatoes.
If potatoes are soft, add a little more flour and cream well.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Spoon into small balls, using 1/2 marshmallow for the center.
Roll in corn flake meal.
Fry in deep oil until brown. Makes about 15 medium balls.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans.
Drain.
Save 1 cup liquid.
Cook meat until no longer pink.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic powder. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add spices.
Cut up tomatoes and add to meat, beans and liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover with lid.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate the cheese.
Add softened cream cheese. Add onion dip and hot sauce.
Mix and form into a ball. Roll in pecans.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese, add sugar.
In another bowl make pudding using milk and instant pudding.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
You can also use cream scrapings from inside of cookies in this mixture.
Layer cookies and pudding in flowerpot, leave plenty of cookie crumbs for topping.
Chill.

title: simple and easy roast
directions: In large saucepan, put a large piece of aluminum foil in pan (enough to wrap roast in).
Place roast in pan, add onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water.
Seal aluminum foil around roast and cook in oven at 325° for approximately 2 hours or when tender with tested with a fork.

title: emerald chicken
directions: Boil the chicken, cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook the package of broccoli and put in bottom of casserole pan.
Add chicken. Combine the soups, margarine and curry.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Put croutons on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese squares
directions: Cut one roll of chocolate chip cookies and put on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Spread in middle.
Cut second roll of chocolate chip cookies (thin).
Spread across top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Mix pineapple juice and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until it thickens.

title: royal seafood
directions: Blend soup with milk and mayonnaise.
Cook rice or pasta. Combine all other ingredients and simmer a few minutes.
Put rice or pasta in 19 x 9-inch casserole and cover with seafood mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add a little milk if it becomes dry.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tomato quiche
directions: In a skillet, saute onion until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook over medium-high heat until liquid is almost evaporated, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Cover with tomato mixture; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in cream; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes or until top begins to brown.
Knife should come out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: amish sauerkraut soup
directions: Fry sausage and drain out excess fat.
If using plain sausage can add herbs:
sage, fennel, thyme or dill.
Return to fire.
Add onion, potatoes and garlic.
Cook on medium until onion is limp and browning.

title: easy cake dessert
directions: Put cherries in baking dish.
Add pineapple on top of cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over all and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350°.

title: john wayne cheese casserole
directions: Combine chilies and cheese and put in buttered casserole dish. Beat egg whites.
Set aside.
Combine egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add egg whites (whites should be creamy).
Pour mixture over cheese and chilies.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate covered pear cake
directions: Slice
each
pear
half
into pieces; arrange on top of cake. Combine
corn
syrup, hot water and butter in saucepan. Heat
to boiling;
remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until	well blended.
Cool.
Cover cake with warm glaze.
Let glaze
set before
decorating with whipped topping.
Makes 12 servings.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in homemade ice cream freezer.

title: pecan crunch snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine the cereal and pecan halves in a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken, pull off bone.
Put in medium bowl.
Add 1/2 can cream of chicken soup; mix this together real well.
Open croissant rolls.
Spoon out chicken mixture in roll, and roll up and put in casserole dish.
Repeat until all is gone.
Take rest of cream of chicken soup, milk and broth and mix in medium bowl until mixed real good.
Pour this over the top of rolls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Ready to eat.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in 7-Up.
Pour lime jello until melted. Have cream cheese room temperature.
Add while still smooth.
Let stand until partly jelled.
Then add mayonnaise, pecans and whipped cream.
Let set until firm, about 4 hours.

title: savory sausage balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg, sausage, stuffing mix and sage; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Add to large skillet; cook over medium heat, turning occasionally.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Remove from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Drain fat from skillet; discard.
Add water, ketchup, chili sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar to skillet; stir well.
Return meatballs to skillet; stir to coat.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cover; reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to chafing dish, if desired.
Serve with wooden picks.
Yield:
about 24 meatballs.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir butter and Parmesan into spaghetti.
Add eggs and toss.
Press mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese on top.
Brown ground meat with onion and pepper until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and spices.
Heat.
Pour over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella and bake for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and butter. Add flour, milk and vanilla. Pour in baking dish. Place peaches and juice on top of batter. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: pasta primavera*
directions: Note:
Save broth where chicken was cooked and cook macaroni in the broth.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of chicken soup

title: hamburger and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook all other ingredients in a skillet and add to macaroni, except cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together and let stand 1 hour.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix together oil, vanilla and eggs.

title: spaghetti with tomatoes and basil(low-fat)
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Add the onion and saute until transparent.
Add the garlic, tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.

title: krispy bar
directions: Melt margarine in a square pan.
Put in marshmallows and then pour mixture over the crisp rice and mix well.
Put in square pan, cut into squares.

title: one-two-three-four cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add the eggs.
Mix with sifted flour and baking powder and add alternately with the milk.
Flavor as desired.
Bake as a loaf or layer cake.
Layers: 375° for 20 minutes.
Loaves:
350° to 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: top of the stove pleaser
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and keep warm.
While noodles cook, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.

title: one step sour cream cake
directions: Allow margarine to come to room temperature.
Add flour, sugar, eggs, salt, soda, vanilla and sour cream.
Beat 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or less.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in larger bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy. Gradually add cool whip and powdered sugar and beat until smooth. Spoon filling in crust. Cover and freeze at least 8 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer vanilla wafers in 9-inch dish.
Slice bananas on top. Spread 1 jar banana glaze over bananas.
Spread 1/2 container Cool Whip over glaze.
Repeat layers.
Pour chocolate syrup over last layer of Cool Whip.
Top with pecans.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Eat and say mm.....mm...good!

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Run hot water over it and drain again.
Melt butter.
Add flour and stir until a smooth paste is formed.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened.
Add seasonings and cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add cooked macaroni and place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake in oven at 350° until crumbs are brown, about 15 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Thoroughly wash and clean spinach leaves. Drain in a large colander. Remove and discard stems. Coarsely chop spinach leaves. Bring 3 cups of water to a boil in a large saucepan. Add spinach. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until the spinach is wilted, about 5 minutes. Drain well. Set aside.

title: basil cream salad
directions: Wash and dry the greens.
Turn whole leaves into a wide salad bowl.
Finely mince the fresh basil leaves.
Sprinkle over the greens.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: orange lemonade punch
directions: Partly freeze a tray of ice cubes.
Put a candy pumpkin or witch in each cube and finish freezing.
Mix together equal amounts of orange and pineapple juice.
Pour into glasses and one ice cube to each glass.
Give each guest a licorice stick to stir his Witch's Brew.

title: english walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold in graham crackers and chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 ungreased 9-inch pie plates.
Spread up onto the sides of the plates.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool shell.
Fill with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until served.
Makes 2 pies.

title: white chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil; add turkey and cook until done. Add rice, beans, corn, chilies, broth and cumin; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until turkey is tender.
Stir in hot pepper sauce to taste.
Serve with shredded cheese; garnish with parsley. Average serving 274 calories, 69 mg. chol., 6 g. fat.

title: cheese-topped pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or line with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt-mix well.
In small bowl, combine pumpkin, milk oil and egg whites, blend well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once, stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter evenly into muffin cups.
Press 1 cube of cream cheese into center of each muffin. Top each with 1/2 tsp brown sugar.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 14 to 18 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center, but not cream cheese, comes out clean.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover pan 2 to 3 minutes to dissolve sugar crystals on side of pan.
Uncover; cook to soft ball stage (240°).
Gradually add hot syrup to egg whites, beating constantly with electric mixer.
Add vanilla; beat until spreading consistency, about 6 minutes.
If too thin, let stand 3 minutes to set up slightly. Stir once or twice.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: german potato salad(cold)
directions: Boil diced potatoes.
Fry diced bacon.
Dice onion, scallions and eggs.
Mix all ingredients and put into large bowl.
Sprinkle top with paprika and chill overnight.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar together to soften.
Add flour and blend.
Form small balls and place half a cherry or walnut on each cookie.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until browned.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while still warm.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, mustard and pepper.
Sprinkle half of the flour mixture over one side of steak; cover with plastic wrap.
In large skillet, brown steak on both sides in hot oil.
Drain off fat; combine water, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon granules.
Pour over steak; spread mushrooms over steak. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake.
While baking, mix Jell-O and boiling water; cool.
Poke holes in cake and pour on Jell-O.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put all ingredients, except meats and tomato paste, in large pot on medium heat.
Brown meat and bake meatballs at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. gards' casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Cut apples in quarters and remove seed (do not peel).
In heavy pot over high heat, cook apples and cider to boiling. Reduce to medium and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until apples are very tender.
Press apple mixture through a sieve.
Return pulp to pot; add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Cook for about 1 hour and 15 minutes until mixture is thick, dark and mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Remove from heat; ladle into jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 10 (8 ounce) jars.

title: easy chicken cordon blue
directions: Heat broiler.
Pound each breast half between two sheets of plastic to 1/4 inch thickness.
Top with slice each of ham and cheese, trimming to fit.
Fold each breast lengthwise in half. Skewer closed on three sides.
Sprinkle chicken with thyme.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes on each side until chicken is cooked and cheese is melted.
Meanwhile prepare vegetables according to package.
Arrange chicken on serving platter, removing skewers.
Spoon vegetables and pasta around chicken.

title: german pork and kraut
directions: Place roast in slow cooker.
Cover with water.
Add next four ingredients.
Cook until roast is tender.
Drain kraut before adding.

title: corn beef spread
directions: Shape into ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: tracy's hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add all ingredients (except 1/2 of cheese).
Stir and bake.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 375° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice from the top of each tomato and scoop out pulp, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Set pulp aside.
In a saucepan, brown mushrooms in oleo.
Add onions, peas, garlic, basil and reserved tomato pulp.
Cook several minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Blend in crisp bread and parsley.
Spoon into tomato shells.
Place in shallow buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water for 10 minutes, uncovered. Drain.
Let chill in the refrigerator.
After chilling, toss beans with mushrooms and onion.
Whisk oil into vinegar; whisk in spices; pour over string beans and toss lightly.
Chill again before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pour half into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Melt in double boiler the caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Remove cake from the oven and pour caramel mixture over it.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Spread the rest of the batter on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Set aside. Mix the remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour half the batter in well greased and floured tube pan.
Pour 1/2 of apple mixture over batter.
Add rest of batter.
Then add remaining apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef on medium heat in large pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove beef from pan and drain grease.
Brown onion and pepper in pan then add ground beef, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste.
Season with garlic powder and oregano.
Add water if necessary to achieve liquid consistency.
Add a liberal amount of brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and allow to simmer 20-30 minutes or longer.
Boil spaghetti in kettle.
Add a bit of vegetable oil to keep noodles from sticking together.
Boil 12-15 minutes.
Drain water.
Serve noodles covered with sauce.

title: vegetable beef and barley soup
directions: In soup pot or Dutch oven, combine water, broth, beef and barley.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium high heat for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, vegetables, and soup.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low, cover pot, and continue to cook for another 20 to 30 minutes or until barley is tender.

title: continental chicken
directions: Spray crock pot with Pam.
Arrange dried beef on bottom of crock pot.
Wrap each piece of chicken in a strip of bacon and lay on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream/flour together. Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on low 8 - 10 hours or high 3 - 5 hours.
Service chicken over cooked rice; soup/beef mixture makes a gravy that can be served over chicken.

title: quick baked pasta
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add to spaghetti sauce.
Boil noodles and drain.
Combine sauce, milk, gravy and Parmesan cheese.
Mix over low heat.
Add noodles and mix real good.
Pour into a 9 x 10-inch cake sheet pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: catholic potatoes
directions: Mash cooked potatoes with beater.
Add all other ingredients and mix well with beater.
Put mixture in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (until golden brown).

title: salmon cheese log
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons of liquid.
Flake.
Combine reserved liquid with salmon, cream cheese, onion and liquid smoke; blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours.
Form mixture into a log 6 to 8-inches long.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Form pimiento into a small bow and place on top center of log for garnish.
Serve with crackers of your choice.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: squash pie
directions: *If plain is used, add 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, softened cream cheese, and sugar together; add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and cool in refrigerator.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone and pull into pieces.
Dip tortillas into boiling broth.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 small pans with tortilla pieces (whole).
Layer chicken; sprinkle onion, etc. Season with chili powder and garlic.
Mix soups together.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Add layer of cheese (sprinkle); start another layer.
After 2 layers, add Ro-Tel and arrange on top (check for Ro-Tel juice to 1/2 depth of casserole; add chicken broth if needed).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl stir together, bran flakes, flour, nuts, soda, salt and sugar.
Make a well in the center.
In another bowl mix beaten eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to flour mixture stirring just until moistened.
Batter will be thick.
Cover and store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
To bake muffins, fill greased cups 3/4 full.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: green pickled tomatoes
directions: Put salt over vegetables; let stand overnight.
Drain well. Add sugar, mustard seed, vinegar and pickling spice.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until tomatoes change color, about fifteen minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry the corn tortillas on both sides to soften.
Drain and dip into enchilada sauce.
In the center of each tortilla place 2 tablespoons ground beef, some olives, onion, and cheese.
Roll up tortillas and fasten with a toothpick.
Add some cheese to the top of the enchiladas.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Mix all into a large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour evenly into pan(s).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat broiler.
Chop mushroom stems and reserve caps.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook mushroom stems, onion and next 4 ingredients until onion is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into caps.
Place caps, stuffed side up, on baking sheet.
Broil 8 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: quick modeling clay
directions: Add water and oil to the dry ingredients to form clay.
Knead. Add food coloring as desired.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine
flour,
soda,
salt,
sugar
and cinnamon in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour
batter
into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake
pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes;
remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks. Spread
frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: french bread croutons
directions: In a bowl toss the diced bread with melted butter and garlic powder.
Brown the bread cubes in a shallow baking dish at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times during browning.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour cans of green beans into large saucepan and cook on high until all moisture is gone.
Put one stick margarine into small saucepan.
Add other ingredients (except cracker crumbs).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle on crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix water, potatoes, onion and salt in a saucepan; cover and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Lower heat and continue cooking for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover and stir gently over low heat until potatoes look dry.
Stir in the remainder of ingredients and heat until cheese melts, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashioned apple loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Stir all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Divide batter evenly into loaf pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Cook in saucepan the water, cocoa, oleo and shortening until it boils.
After mixture boils, add it to flour and sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, salt, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: In a large kettle, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned. Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, beans, paste, beer, chili powder, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Serve with chopped raw onions, jalapeno peppers and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and spread evenly.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Add cake mix over cherries and spread.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Slice butter in pats and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir into beaten eggs and milk. Add corn.
Pour into greased casserole and place lump of butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 3 or 4 generously.

title: banana-nut waffles
directions: Beat all ingredients with wire whisk or electric mixer until almost smooth.
Pour generous 1 cup batter onto center of hot waffle iron sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake until steaming stops, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Yields three 9-inch waffles.

title: rhineland-german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into thin slices.
Cook in boiling salted water 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils and place in cooking utensil.
Add enough water to cover.
Cook until partly done.

title: cake frosting
directions: *I like to add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan, then spread cherries on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of cherries.
Pour butter over cake mix.
Cover with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Place rice and onion soup mix in a casserole dish.
Place chicken ove this and spread the soup on top.
Pour can of water over the chicken mixture.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: apricot-pineapple-pecan cheese ball
directions: Stir cream cheese until smooth and add grated cheese;
stir in drained pineapple, red peppers, onions, seasonings and 1 cup of the nuts.
Turn out onto a sheet of plastic wrap and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Roll ball in remaining 1 cup of nuts to coat.
Thin the preserves slightly with a tablespoon of water and stir well.
Pour preserves over the cheese ball and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peaches supreme
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and preserves; blend well.
Stir in pineapple.
Slice a small portion from the base of each peach half so that the fruit sits flat; reserve peach slices. Arrange peach halves on serving plates.
Spoon 1/4 of pineapple mixture into each peach half; sprinkle with pecans.
Garnish each with reserved peach slices and mint leaves. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange-glazed pork chops
directions: For glaze, in a small saucepan, stir together the sugar, cornstarch, orange peel, ginger root and red pepper.
Stir in orange juice and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Trim any separable fat from the chops.
Place chops on the unheated rack of a broiler pan. Broil 3 to 4 inches from the heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, turning once.
Brush the chops with the glaze frequently during broiling.
Serve with the remaining glaze.

title: hot bean dish
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add ketchup, vinegar, mustard and sugar.
Stir in beans.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: seven layer squares
directions: Pour butter into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add ingredients in layers in order listed; do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pam one
9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches into pan.
Pour sugar over
peaches.
Sprinkle
peach
jello
mix
over sugar. Pour cake mix over entire mixture.
Cut up stick of margarine over cake mix.
Pour	water over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook carrot, celery and onion in 1 cup boiling salted water for 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not drain.
Melt butter in a saucepan. Add flour and stir until well blended (about 2 minutes).
Slowly add milk and broth; cook while stirring until smooth and thickened.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Just before serving, add cheese to flour and broth mixture.
When blended, add vegetables with cooking water.
Stir constantly over low heat until smooth.

title: green bean, walnut, mint and feta salad
directions: In a pot with a vegetable basket and water up to the basket, place green beans.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat, simmering for about 10 minutes.
Remove vegetables from pot and run cold water over them.
Refrigerate.

title: orange-cranberry sauce
directions: In a large (3-quart) microwave-safe dish, combine first 2 ingredients.
Microwave, covered with vented lid or plastic wrap, on full power for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Add sugar and mix well.
Cover and let stand.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crabmeat.
Fold in crabmeat. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine milk, sugar and margarine; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Reduce to medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts; beat until well blended.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and cut into squares when firm.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray pie plate with Pam.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into pie pan.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 4 or 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: blender banana cake
directions: In blender, puree bananas to make 1 cup.
Add oil and eggs. Blend well.
In a medium bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Pour in banana mix.
Mix until just blended.
Pour into prepared 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Rap on table to remove bubbles. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes, until center springs back.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hoosier corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add eggs, slightly beaten, and sour cream. Put in 2 cans of corn and the muffin mix.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, more or less.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Put in jars and seal.
Use large porcelain container.
Eat with chips.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Use iron fry or cheese cake pan.
Use large bowl for adding each step.

title: microwaved cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Use paper liners in muffin pan.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each of 6 liners.
Soften cream cheese on 1/2 power for 1 minute. Blend in egg, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 to 2/3rds full.
Microwave on 1/2 power for 3 1/2 minutes or until cheese cake begins to set.
Remove from muffin pan.
Place a spoonful of pie filling over each cheese cake.
Cool before serving.
Yields 12.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix bananas, pineapple juice, lemon juice, orange juice, and sugar together.
Chill.
Just before serving, add the 7-Up.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown garlic and sausage or chicken. Add onion and green pepper and saute. Add tomatoes and water and simmer for 1/2 hour. Add rice and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine
semi-sweet
chips
and
unsweetened
chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts in
a
large
bowl.
Combine
sugar, salt, evaporated milk and butter in large heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour
at
once over chocolate mixture.
Stir vigorously with
wooden spoon until chocolate is melted and mixture is creamy.
Pour
into
buttered shallow 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand a few
hours to set.
Cut into squares. Store in metal box.

title: orange-rice jello fluff salad or dessert
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve with chicken. Serves 9 to 12.

title: brown sugar cookies with butterscotch chips
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then drop by spoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer in this order:
chicken, cheese, Doritos, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix together soups and tomatoes in bowl before adding to rest of ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: treasure cake
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Put in 13 x 9-inch or 2 round pans. Grease and flour pans.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown on top at 350°.

title: brunch sausage casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart square baking dish.
Set aside.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook the sausage until browned, stirring to break up the meat.
Drain on paper towels.
Cook the grits according to package directions, omitting the salt.
Stir in the butter or margarine until melted. Stir in the sausage, eggs, milk, salt and 1 1/4 cups of the cheese.
Spread the sausage mixture in the prepared baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle the casserole with the remaining cheese.
Bake for 2 1/2 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then serve.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Then mix mayonnaise, bacon, sugar and cheese.
Spread on top.
Cover tight and let set 24 hours.
Mix just before serving.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch pieces.

title: peanut butter tandycakes
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
While beating, add sugar gradually.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; blend into beaten mixture.
Beat in vanilla.
Let butter melt in milk as it heats.
When small bubbles form around edge of pan, pour hot milk into batter.
Beat to blend thoroughly.
Grease pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately spread peanut butter on hot cake; refrigerate.
Place chocolate bars on cake; put in oven until chocolate melts.
Spread and refrigerate.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In a blender or food processor, chop cranberries until fine. Peel 2 oranges and chop finely.
Grind other oranges with skin in blender until fine.
Mix all ingredients and add sugar to taste. Chill and serve.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix syrup, butter, salt, flavoring and sugar.
Knead well. Add chopped pecans. Roll into logs.
Brush with Karo syrup.
Roll in pecans.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Turn burner on low heat.
Combine yolks and lemon juice in small pot.
Beat with a whisk until frothy.
Divide butter in thirds, add one third to the pot at a time.
Stir constantly until all butter is in and melted.
Let it thicken gradually.
Don't leave on heat.
Keep stirring.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken. Place chicken, skin sides down, in pan.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and put yolks in bowl.
Mash yolks; add cream cheese.
Mash with fork to get all lumps out. Add remaining ingredients except bacon and pickle juice.
Mix well.
Add pickle juice a little at a time to get the consistency you like, not too loose.
Refill egg whites.
Sprinkle tops with bacon crumbs. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Recipe may be doubled and freeze 1 for later use.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter.
Mix and press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine crem cheese, confectioners sugar and one carton Cool Whip.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cooled cake.
Refrigerate.

title: tangy gelatin salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add gelatin and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp; crumble.
Brown the onion and celery in the bacon grease until tender.
Put everything together except for the milk.
Cover and cook until the potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add milk; heat and serve.

title: mushroom cheeseburger pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll dough and place in greased pan.
Starting at center, press out with hands.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: california rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover; let stand overnight without refrigeration.
Next morning, roll dough the size of a 9-inch pie pan (1/2 inch thick).
Cut into pie shape wedges.
Roll from large end and place on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise.
Can stay up to 8 hours.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: old southern beaten biscuits(heritage)
directions: In a small mixing bowl stir together the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Cut in the lard until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center of dry mixture. Add 3/4 cup ice water all at once; stir well.
Add enough additional ice water to make a stiff dough.
Turn out the dough on a lightly floured surface.
Beat vigorously with the flat side of mallet or hammer for 15 minutes, turning and folding the dough constantly.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness and cut with 2-inch cutter.
Dip cutter in flour between cuts to prevent sticking. Place the biscuits on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick each biscuit top 3 times with a fork.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.
Makes 24.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion into bowl and mix well.
In separate bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour on top of broccoli mix.
Chill and serve.

title: mushroom medley
directions: In skillet, saute first four ingredients for 3 minutes on medium.
Add mushrooms; cook for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bring to a boil in pot, beef broth and cream; stir in cornstarch.
Stir until thickens.
Pour into mushrooms.
Serve as a side dish or garnish the top of a steak or grilled boneless chicken breast.

title: diabetic oatmeal-peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine and mix in milk and cocoa. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter, oatmeal and sugar substitute. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper or greased cookie sheet. Keep frozen. Recipe yields 24 small cookies. One calorie per cookie.

title: frigidaire cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add drained pineapple to mixture.
Add nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Roll vanilla wafers to crumbs.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 crumbs. Pour mixture over crumbs and spread remaining crumbs over top.
Let stand overnight.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: strawberry streusel pizza
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry cake mix, oats and butter until blended. Set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Add egg to the remaining crumb mixture and mix well. Press into a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Build up the edges and flute, if desired. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and gelatin. Add oil; beat in eggs, one at a time. Add berries and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine pudding mix and milk, beat 2 to 3 minutes until very thick.
Fold in whipped topping, pineapple and lemon juice. Pour into crust and refrigerate overnight or 4 hours. Top with whipped topping.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well.
Shape into small cakes and fry in butter over medium heat until browned.

title: apea cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add shortening.
Mix egg in cup, then add milk to equal 1 cup.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 3 small (8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all together in blender.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir soup until smooth; mix with milk.
Add beans and 1/2 cup onions.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Sprinkle other onions over top; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix cake mix,
1 egg and butter and press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking
dish.
Top	with chocolate chips and nuts.	Mix confectioners
sugar, remaining 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake
mix
base and bake at 350° until bubbly and golden, about 30 minutes.

title: bernie's peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 5 minutes until golden brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup. Blend well.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly brown and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Do not microwave again.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased aluminum foil on a cookie sheet.
Let cool, 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into smaller pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: three cheese enchiladas
directions: Combine 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup picante sauce, red pepper, onions, and cumin and mix well. Spoon 1/4 cup cheese mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll and place seam down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spoon remaining picante sauce evenly over enchiladas; cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until hot.
Top with lettuce and tomato and serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dragon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
You may use a double boiler on low-medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and blended.
Add bacon.
Keep hot in chafing dish. Serve with crackers, apple wedges and fresh vegetable sticks.

title: amish cookies
directions: Soften butter; add sugar and cream.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over the 100% Bran.
Cool.
Mix salt, soda, flour and All-Bran.
Cream Crisco and sugar well and add beaten eggs, buttermilk and the cooled bran.
Add the dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add raisins or dates, if desired.
Bake in greased or lined muffin tins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter can be stored in covered container in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks, letting you bake as many as you wish.
This recipe will make about 3 dozen muffins.

title: kimberly's broccoli & grape salad
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Set aside. Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over vegetables. Mix well.
Allow to marinate overnight.

title: chili con carne a la antigua(guatemala)
directions: In a stew pot, saut the garlic and onion in the oil until soft.
Add the ground beef and cook until well done.
Drain the oil from the pot and add the canned tomatoes, water, fresh tomatoes, green chile, spices, and red beans.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 -3 hours.
Serve in soup bowls and top with the grated cheese.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Break up tortilla chips and place in bottom of casserole dish, then layer chicken over chips.
Mix together soups, tomatoes (chopped), juice and all, milk, onions and bell pepper and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes or until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Let cool 25 minutes.
Poke holes with fork on top of cake.
Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and pour over cake.
Chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain thoroughly.
Mix sour cream and soup mix and blend with drained spinach.
Top with croutons and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Then dredge the fruit and nuts lightly with 2 tablespoons flour.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned in 350° oven.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom of well-greased 15 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix softened margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls of dollops onto cake mix. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until done.
Very rich.
Serve small pieces.

title: barbecue in crock-pot
directions: Rub roast with brown sugar and place in crock-pot.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low for 11 to 12 hours.
Shred meat with fork. Drain liquid.
Save 1 cup from bottom.
Replace meat in crock-pot and add all of ingredients.
Skim the fat off of saved liquid; add to meat.
Stir well and cook for 4 to 5 hours more.

title: french toast overnight
directions: Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla extract and pour over French bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Melt butter in pan.
Shake potatoes in bag of flour until coated.
Roll each piece in melted butter.
Shake Parmesan cheese over potatoes.
Salt to taste. Bake in oven (350°) for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on size of potatoes.
Cover with foil for soft, moist potatoes.
Keep uncovered for a crispy potato.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, both soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown. Let stand at least 5 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Boil the sugar, water and Karo until it reaches 250°.
Then beat the egg whites until stiff.
After syrup boils, beat together the egg whites until it clings to a spoon and stiff.
Pour out on Saran Wrap on confectioners sugar.
Knead like dough.
Flatten, then spread with peanut butter and roll up.
Then cut in slices.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas and let stand. Cream sugar shortening, and unbeaten eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix with a spoon. Stir in bananas, vanilla, and nuts. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart glass bowl.
Microwave for 14 to 15 minutes on High, or until hot and bubbly (about 160°). Stir, remove spices and serve.
Makes about 8 (8 ounce) servings.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until light, add sugar and beat 2 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a shallow pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, cut into bars and roll in confectioner's sugar.
Raisins, figs, or currants can be used instead of dates.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken, salt, water, vinegar, onion, chicken broth, carrots and celery in large soup kettle, adding more water if necessary to cover the chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until meat almost falls off the bones. Strain the broth and reserve the meat.
Remove skin and bones from the chicken.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Bring broth and chicken to a boil.
Tear or cut biscuits into pieces and drop into the boiling broth.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brown paper bag apple pie
directions: Mix all of these ingredients and put in pie shell.
Add topping and bake in paper bag in 425° oven for 1 hour.

title: glen's hot wings
directions: Spread wings out in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and place on stove until it comes to boil.
Let mixture cool, then pour over wings.
Let stay in refrigerator 24 hours. Take wings and flour and fry in deep fryer until done!
Look out for the fire when you bite 'em.
Mmm-good!

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix butter in hot applesauce.
Combine other ingredients with the flour and add the applesauce gradually.
Add soda and water last.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 36 cupcakes.
Ice with brown sugar icing.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook lima beans according to package directions; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Add lima beans and water chestnuts.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish that has been lightly greased.
Cook and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together like pie crumbs.
Save 1 cup and set aside for top of cake.
Add molasses and mix well. Stir the baking soda into the hot water.
Pour over mixture and mix well.
Divided into 2 layer cake pans or one 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Cut hot dogs in half.
Wrap 1 biscuit around each half-hot dog.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Bake according to directions on biscuit can.
Makes a great snack.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix milk, soup and pepper.
Fill each tortilla with chicken mixture, cheese and soup.
Place tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: maryland crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1 cup of cheese.
Place mixture in 10-inch Pyrex dish (pie plate). Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Gradually stir milk in the sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well.
Mix mayo, vegetable mix and sour cream. Add well drained spinach.
Chill.
tags: Mrs. Grass vegetable soup dry mix

title: skillet okra with shrimp
directions: In a large skillet fry bacon. Remove bacon when done.	Pour off excess grease except for 1/4 cup.
Add cut okra to grease and seasonings.
Crumble bacon on top.	Let simmer for 10 minutes. Add shrimp to okra.
Let cook 10 minutes or until shrimp is pink. Serve over white rice.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain vermicelli noodles.
Add Italian dressing, Kroger salad seasoning, tomatoes and bell peppers.
Chill for several hours.
Makes approximately 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add orange juice.
Mix well.
Serve with sliced apples and other fruit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon and salt.
Mix well.
Chill and shape into ball.
Roll in pecans and serve with crackers.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: german oven pancake
directions: Gradually add flour to eggs, beating with beater.
Stir in milk, melted oleo and salt.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch skillet.
Pour batter into cold skillet.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple chiffon salad
directions: Put pineapple in 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O. Let cool; add 3 tablespoons pineapple juice in cream cheese.
Mix together, then whip Carnation evaporated milk.
Add cream cheese mixture, then add pineapple mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices; toss with oil. Place in a single layer in a 13 x 9 greased baking pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir 1/2 hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Blend hot mixture into saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in butter and vanilla.

title: strata
directions: *You can use 2 kinds; for example, Cheddar and Monterey Jack.

title: grandma's spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in oil, add onions and garlic; saute. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Bring to a boil. Put rice in and cook very slow; add water if needed. Cook until tender. Sprinkle grated cheese on top; let melt.

title: fruit soup
directions: Mix tapioca, sugar, salt and water until thick and clear. Drain strawberries and peaches and save the juices.
Drain mandarin oranges and grapes, but don't save juices.
After cooking the first group of ingredients, add 1 1/2 cups of the juices from strawberries and peaches and the orange juice.
Add mandarin oranges and grapes.
Add bananas when served.
Mixture will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all other ingredients. Add flour mixture.
Bake in muffin tins for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 20 to 24 popsicle or craft sticks.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg, vanilla and butter flavoring, beating until blended.
Combine flour and soda; add to shortening mixture alternately with bananas, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3rds full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 15 muffins.

title: easy homemade split pea soup
directions: Rinse peas.
Boil in water for about 1 hour.
Add salt, thyme, garlic and pepper.
Add chopped carrots, celery and onion.
Stir in diced ham.
Simmer 1 more hour until vegetables are tender.
Serve with fresh crusty bread and a dollop of sour cream.

title: hot potato and sauerkraut salad
directions: Slice celery and onions.
Put potatoes in a large pan; fill with cold water just to top of potatoes.
Heat on high (no lid) until it starts to boil.
After a full boil, remove from heat (test that fork will easily go into potatoes, but do not overcook).
Run cold water over potatoes to cool; drain all water off and set aside.
Add enough water to sauerkraut liquid to make 1 cup.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together.
Sprinkle instant pudding over fruit.
Mix Tang and pineapple juice.
Pour liquid mixture over fruit and stir.
Chill at least one hour.
(Instead of mandarin oranges, any seasonal fruit can be used.)

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender. Drain off fat. Combine meat and onion with noodles, cheese, soup, 1 cup water, green pepper, chili sauce, pimiento, salt and dash of pepper. Mix well. Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine crumbs and butter. Sprinkle atop. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot. Trim with green pepper rings, if desired. Serves 12.

title: stuffed cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers in half; scoop out seeds.
Salt and turn over on paper towel to drain.
Mix cream cheese, peppers, onion and paprika together.
Stuff mixture into the hollowed out cucumbers; wrap in foil and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and serve as salad or hors d'oeuvre!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding in pineapple; fold in marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: quiche
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a bowl using a hand mixer or blender until frothy.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Precook crust 10 minutes.
Layer each pie bottom with a cup of sharp cheese, shredded.
Pour egg mixture over cheese, being careful to divide mixture equally.
Place on center rack and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 pies.

title: sweet and hot pickles
directions: Drain vinegar off pickles; slice pickles. Put back in jar. Fill jar with sugar (usually only holds 4 pounds).
Add bottle of Tabasco sauce; replace lid. Place upside down in icebox. Take jar and shake once a day for a week.

title: orange icing
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Beat in 2 cups sugar.
Blend in milk, orange peel and vanilla.
Add remaining 2 cups of sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook in pie crust until done, about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
