directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut into pieces.
Place in 7 x 11-inch (or larger) buttered dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and combine with poppy seed.
Sprinkle on soup mixture.
Melt margarine and dribble on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix cheeses and mayonnaise; stir in onion.
Top with almonds and bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes until cheeses are melted or heat in microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: crispy baked chicken livers
directions: Clean and cut livers in half.
Mix crumbs and seasoning salt. Dip livers in oleo, then roll in crumbs.
Arrange in buttered casserole.
Pour rest of oleo over all.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 minutes.
Turn each one over after 15 minutes.

title: bourbon brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Cream the butter and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add melted chocolate and blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour and baking powder and stir into the chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and mix. Last, stir in the bourbon.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake approximately 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Ice with Chocolate Bourbon Icing, leaving out the nuts.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in margarine.
Work dough with hands if it seems dry.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around olives.
Shape into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients until moist.
Do not knead!
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken primo
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put deboned chicken in bottom of dish.
Spread sour cream over chicken.
Sprinkle dry Stove Top over sour cream.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted oleo over Stove Top.
Pour 1 cup broth over oleo.
Top with mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheesy crabmeat dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese.
Add softened cream cheese and mix.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Alternate layers of squash, bits of butter, pimento and soup in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter tossed together.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until brown. May be made ahead of time and baked later.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Bring Coke and cocoa to a boil.
Add to butter mixture; add vanilla and buttermilk, soda, flour and marshmallows and pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets 2 hours, until soft like a potato. Pour water off and put in cold water. Peel (skin should come right off). Cut in chunks or slices. Then make juice with remaining ingredients. Put beets in juice and bring to a boil. Then put hot beets in jars and tighten to seal.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add ground beef to onion and cook until the beef loses its pink color.

title: brunch casserole for 8
directions: Place scrambled eggs in buttered shallow baking dish.
Add milk to mushroom soup.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour over eggs the can of mushrooms, green onions, water chestnuts and Parmesan cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: old fashioned au gratin potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes and slice thin. Cook onions and margarine until onions are clear. Stir in flour, salt and pepper, cooking over low heat until bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart pan. Pour cheese sauce over. Cook, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour or 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Combine remaining cheese and bread crumbs and top final 15 minutes of baking.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Stir in beans; heat until
bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil and stir well. Add eggs, cinnamon and carrots and stir together.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or longer, until it springs back.

title: brunch rolls
directions: Place nuts in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan.
Arrange rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle pudding and cinnamon evenly over rolls. In saucepan, heat brown sugar and oleo.
Once mixed well, drizzle evenly over rolls.
Place pan in a cold oven and let stand overnight.
Next morning, turn oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes, then turn out of pan.

title: caramel icing(never fail)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and boil for 2 minutes (after it comes slowly to a boil).
Take off fire and add baking powder and vanilla.
Beat well until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cake. Double recipe for a layer cake if you wish.
I find this enough for 2 layers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add bananas and nuts.
Grease and flour a loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place pie shell in dish; mix all ingredients.
Place in pie shell and top with second sheet of pastry.
Prick several holes in top and bake at 425° until crust is golden brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and oil; add sugar gradually; beating well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa three times.
Finish making 1 cup with water added to evaporated milk.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Put vanilla in the milk.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, green pepper and onion in blender or by hand. Chopped cabbage should equal about 3 cups.
Combine other ingredients in large bowl. Add cabbage, pepper and onion; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin and sugar.
Mix in dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Grease cookie sheet with lard or Crisco.
Line with wax paper and grease again.
Coat both sides of wax paper.
Pour batter onto prepared cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake out on a towel. Cover tea towel with powdered sugar so will cover cake area.
Roll with towel; let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown floured ribs in shortening.
Put in small roaster. Combine rest of ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Add more water, as needed.

title: cathy janke's tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine (or margarine and shortening) until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and salt, one cup at a time.
Add only as much as needed to roll out dough and cut cookies without dough falling apart.
(This will be about 3 cups for a single recipe.
Use fourth cup for rolling out.)
Add vanilla; mix well.
Roll out to about 3/8-inch thickness or thinner if desired.
Bake at 350° to 375° until lightly browned on edges.

title: macaroni and ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt, pepper and onions, then sauce. Boil macaroni (use teaspoon of grease to keep from sticking). Pour off leftover water, run cold water over macaroni.
Place pot back on stove, heat on medium.
Add ground beef, small can of tomato sauce.
Stir and let cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with salad and whole kernel corn.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter
well,
adding
sugar
gradually.
Add egg yolks, well
beaten,
and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pastry shells and bake
in moderate oven until firm and brown.
Cover with meringue made
from the remaining egg whites and slightly brown.
This makes 2 pies.

title: easy as pie "dough"
directions: Remove 1/4 cup flour from the 2 cups.
Add 1/3 cup water to make a paste.
Crumble Crisco in flour until like corn meal.
Add paste; mix with hands.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until done at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar in a small bowl.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead 10 minutes until smooth.
Place dough in a greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place 1 hour, until dough is doubled in bulk. Pinch off dough the size of a golf ball.
Roll into a 15-inch rope with hands.
Make a loop, bringing left end over to the right and the right under the left.
Bring ends over and down.
Press ends against the sides of the loop.
Preheat oven to 425° while forming the pretzels.
Place pretzels on a baking sheet, leaving spreading room.
Brush with beaten egg to which a little water has been added.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: chicken pauline
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Cover each piece with a slice of cheese, then mushrooms and soup (undiluted).
Spread stuffing mix over chicken.
Pour butter over stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spread on bottom of dish. Layer salsa then sour cream.
Sprinkle lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives and onions on top.
Serve with nachos.

title: date balls
directions: Mix butter, dates and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Cool, roll into balls and roll these into the powdered sugar.

title: copper carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots 1/8 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cook in salted water about 10 minutes.
Carrots should be a little crisp.
Drain and cool in colander.
Place green pepper and onion in a large bowl with a tight cover and set aside.
Combine tomato soup, salad oil, sugar, dry mustard and vinegar in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Pour marinade over pepper and onion; let cool. When marinade is cooled and carrots are cooled, add carrots to marinade with pepper and onions.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
This keeps well in the refrigerator for weeks.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan. blend in milk and syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in butter and vanilla. Cool.

title: allies heavenly salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add strawberry jello, and both puddings.
Boil 2 minutes.
Set in refrigerator until hard.
Add frozen strawberries and mix with spoon.
Fold in cool whip.
You can use orange jello and mandarin oranges if desired.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg lightly and add sugar.
Add the apples and nuts; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.
Very good.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes.
Reserve liquid.
Mix together tomatoes and reserved liquid, onion, green beans, okra, green pepper, lemon juice and herbs.
Cover and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix in zucchini and eggplant and continue baking, covered, 60 more minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese just before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry slush
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add tea bags.
Soak them in water for 5 minutes.
Add the sugar and let it cool.
Next, add the grape juice, lemonade, schnapps and 7 cups of water.
Stir these together.
Freeze this mixture 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Boil noodles in the reserved broth.
Set aside. Mix Ro-Tel and the two soups.
Layer noodles, chicken, soup mixture and slices
of cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Great to prepare night before.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet real chocolate morsels and nuts.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, milk and corn.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Layer all fresh ingredients in a bowl (I use a trifle bowl) in a pleasing color arrangement.
Place frozen peas on top.
Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle with the sugar.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, cover with a layer of shredded cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: 15 minute meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, salt, peppers, onion and 1/2 tomato sauce. Press into a greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in bottom shelf of oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cook under broiler until brown.
Combine remaining sauce with brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce and pour over meat.

title: candied apples
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling.
Flavor as desired.
Pare and quarter each apple.
Cut each quarter in thirds.
Cook apples, a few pieces at a time, until clear and transparent.
Drain.
Place on waxed paper.
Let dry 24 hours.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: indian pudding
directions: Bring 1 pint milk to a boil.
Stir in the corn meal; cook until thick.
Put into a baking dish.
Add 1 quart milk, corn syrup or molasses, salt, raisins and ginger.
Bake, stirring often, for about 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven until thick.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter; sift in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add peanut butter and 2/3 cup milk.
Mix until all flour is dampened and then beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Add rest of milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans lined with wax paper or rectangular cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook lasagna; drain.
Combine spinach, cheese, egg and cheese from package.
Spread a tablespoon of spinach mixture along the length of lasagna macaroni.
Roll up and place curly edge side up in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Repeat with remaining lasagna and spinach mixture.
Pour sauce from package over Spinach Roll-Ups and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour in large skillet.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: nana's pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix and press into dish, butter, sugar and pretzels.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine with egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with pumpkin.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wayne's champagne salad
directions: Blend together sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Stir in pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Serve partially frozen.
Thaw 20 minutes before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Add soda and water. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snails
directions: Remove crust from sliced white bread.
Roll out bread with rolling pin.
Spread cream cheese over bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up slices of bread.
Slice the rolled up creation into four or five pinwheel type slices.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is hot and bread is starting to brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Toss gently to mix; let stand 30 minutes.
Rinse and drain well; pat dry with paper towels.
In same bowl, mix together vinegar and sugar.
Add cucumbers and mix gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Drain before serving.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in an oblong baking dish and place dish in oven to melt margarine.
Pour drained peaches over melted margarine and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Mix remaining ingredients to form a batter and pour over fruit. Sprinkle cinnamon over all and bake for 35 minutes.
Serve plain with a sprinkling of powdered sugar or with a dollop of Cool Whip. Serves 8.

title: asparagus stir-fry
directions: Mix the broth, soy sauce and cornstarch together.
Set aside. Melt the butter in a nonstick skillet and saute onions until golden brown.
Add asparagus and stir.
Fry for 3 minutes; add the broth mixture.
Cook and stir until the sauce is clear.
Makes 4 servings.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs.
Set aside.
In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, sugar & vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Just before serving pour dressing over salad, toss and serve.
6-8 servings.

title: one dish chicken & stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing with 1/2 c. boiling water and 1 Tbsp. margarine. Spoon stuffing across center of 2 qt. shallow baking dish.
Place chicken on each side of stuffing.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Mix soup, milk, and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 6.

title: cool whip cake
directions: Cook cake mix and leave in pan. Heat milk and sugar in microwave; punch holes in warm cake and pour milk over cake. Let cool and top with Cool whip, then with coconut.

title: oven fried potatoes(2 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with no-stick cooking spray.
Wash and scrub potato. Cut lengthwise into eighths.
Dip potato into combined egg white and water and then into combined remaining ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: sugarless cake(for diabetics)
directions: Put raisins, dates, orange and nuts through food chopper.
Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, soda and salt together.
Add to fruit mixture.
Beat egg and add to mixture along with milk, melted shortening and vanilla.
Mix altogether and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cheese squares
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.

title: company ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into balls.
Place in shallow pan.

title: eighteen-eighty-six cheese soup(the 1886 room, the old driskill hotel, austin, tx)
directions: Saute vegetables in butter; add flour and cornstarch.
Put vegetables in top of double boiler.
Add milk and chicken stock. Heat.
Add soda and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add remaining seasonings.
Serve hot topped with dash of paprika.

title: baked spaghetti and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole pan or dish.
Brown ground beef with garlic and onion; drain.
Add drained mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as usual.
Place half of cooked spaghetti in bottom of casserole. Spread out and add half of the ground beef mixture on top.
Add half of American cheese, sprinkle on Parmesan cheese, then add Swiss cheese, then half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat all layers.
Bake 25 minutes until golden brown on top.
Serve piping hot.
May be made in advance and frozen.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking powder and spices.
Mix oil with dry ingredients, add eggs and persimmon pulp.
Mix in nuts, dates and raisins.
Grease 2 standard size loaf pans or three 1-pound coffee cans and 1 large Bundt pan, or 1 small Bundt pan and 1 loaf pan, or 6 small loaf pans.
Baking times will vary according to size of pan used but the standard loaf pan will take about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick-cook chili
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in pinto beans, tomato soup and chili powder.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach salad (celebrity favorite)
directions: Blend all ingredients together except the cheese and pour over peas.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Cover and chill for 12 hours.
Do not toss.
Serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk and margarine over medium high heat; cook until rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute and 45 seconds.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
(Can add marshmallows, nuts or raisins.)

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir flour mixture into sweet potato mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or just until cakes center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Turn onto platter to complete cooling.
May ice with vanilla or cream cheese icing, if preferred.

title: italian chicken
directions: Beat together egg and oil.
Dip chicken in mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Mix tomato paste, onion powder, oregano, basil, garlic salt and bouillon.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Five minutes before serving, place Mozzarella cheese over chicken and melt in oven. Serve with spaghetti and top with sauce.

title: potato soup
directions: Barely cover potatoes, onion and celery with water; cook until tender.
Add milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve topped with chopped parsley.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unwrap caramels.
Make German chocolate cake according to directions on box, then pour one-half of the batter into prepared pan.
Bake half the batter for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: "colleen's very own clam dip"
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lazy pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and baking soda.
Bake 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes. Coat popcorn.
Use large roasting pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry gelatin over cottage cheese.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple; stir gently to mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt, if desired, taco mix, onion and tomatoes.
Cook slowly.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/2 corn and corn bread mix.
Blend well.
Pour 1/2 batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with beef, cheese and remaining corn.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: southern classic chess pie
directions: Stir together sugar and next 7 ingredients until blended. Add eggs, stirring well. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, shielding edges with foil after 10 minutes to prevent excessive browning. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Saute the onion and mushrooms in the oil until tender. Add the spinach and ham. Mix the eggs, cheese and pepper. Spread into 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until knife comes clean.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Chop nuts and set aside.
Beat eggs 35 to 40 seconds or until lemon colored.
Add granulated sugar.
Combine thoroughly until slightly thickened.
Add lemon juice and pumpkin just until mixed. Stir together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Add to wet ingredients just until flour disappears. Do not overmix.
Spread batter in greased and floured pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto terry cloth towel sprinkled with a little powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together with nuts on outside of roll.
Cool seam side down on rack.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook and drain meat; put in 1-quart pan.
Add all ingredients. Cook on high to a boil, then turn lower to simmer for about 30 minutes or until green peppers are tender.
If thicker is preferred, add 4 ounce can of tomato paste.

title: grape walnut salad
directions: Toss main ingredients and fruit in large bowl.
Mix salad dressing and lemon juice.
Mix dressing with main ingredients. Yield 6 servings.

title: chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Cook for 5 minutes.
Then pour over chicken and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: butterflies
directions: Cut butter and flour together; stir in sour
cream and lemon peel.
Shape into a 4 1/2-inch square; place on waxed paper and refrigerate 2 hours. Cut dough into 4 pieces; work with one piece of dough at a

time. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar on wax paper surface; coat dough in sugar. Roll dough into a 12 x 5-inch rectangle, flipping often. (Do not re-roll dough scraps.) On 12-inch edge, mark center. From each short end, roll dough to center mark. Wrap rolls and refrigerate 2 hours. Cut chilled rolls into 3/8-inch slices.
Dip each slice into sugar on both sides. Bake on foil-lined baking sheets at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Turn over; bake 3 minutes more. Cool on wire rack. Yield: 40 cookies.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; if color desired add package of Jell-O in color desired.
Add ice and punch fruit ring.

title: peggy's scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk and beat until fluffy.
Fold in bread and pineapple.
Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until mixture bubbles and top browns.
Great with ham or pork dishes.

title: quick banana dessert(lo-fat, lo-cal)
directions: In a bowl, whisk or beat milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes, until soft set. Fold in half of the whipped topping. Place 9 graham cracker squares in an ungreased baking dish. Top with half of the pudding mixture, then half of the sliced bananas. Then put another layer of crackers, pudding mixture and sliced bananas. Top with remaining whipped topping. Let set, covered, in the refrigerator for at least an hour before serving.

title: kielbasa treats
directions: Mix jelly and ketchup in saucepan over very low heat until mixture is smooth.
Add cubes or slices of kielbasa.
Heat through and serve with toothpicks.
(Also may use Lil' Wieners or meatballs instead of kielbasa.)
Excellent for parties!!

title: nacho cheese melt
directions: Place chips on microwave plate.
Cover chips with slices of cheese.
Place in microwave for 35 to 40 seconds.
Any additional toppings (optional).
Take out and enjoy!

title: old-fashioned chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven; discard vegetables and bay leaf.
Let chicken cool; skin, bone, and cut into bite-size pieces.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
rice in water and salt.
Saute celery, onions and broccoli
in
margarine.
Mix cooked rice and sauteed ingredients. Add
soup
and cheese.
Mix and bake in baking dish for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine water and sauce in a bowl. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with approximately 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Arrange a layer of uncooked noodles over the sauce. Spread half the Mozzarella over the sauce and sprinkle over 2 tablespoons Parmesan.

Spread approximately 1 1/2 cups sauce over the cheeses, layer of noodles, then cheeses. Top with a layer of noodles. Pour remaining sauce over noodles and spread evenly to cover edges. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly with foil and set on a jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove foil for the last 1/2 hour of baking time.
Let stand on rack for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: macaroon au chocolat
directions: Melt wax in a double boiler, then add other ingredients; cornflakes go in last.
Drop onto waxed paper to cool and harden.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Take 2 Ritz crackers, put chunky peanut butter between them. Dip in melted white chocolate.
Put on wax paper.
Sprinkle candy sprinkles over them.

title: florida fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon and remove.
Add onion to drippings.
Saute until lightly browned.
You may add chopped bacon to chowder if you desire.
Add water and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are almost done.
Cut fillets into pieces, approximately 1-inch square.
Add fish to mixture and cook until fish flakes when tested with fork. Pour in milk and seasonings.
Heat and serve.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place 1 c. pecans in unbaked pie shell. Mix eggs, sugar and flour together. Add syrup, vanilla and salt. Pour over pecans in pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: christmas balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chopped fruit.
Roll in hand into balls and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow hats
directions: Melt chocolate with oil in top of double boiler.
Pour coconut into a shallow dish.
Dip each marshmallow into chocolate, then coat with coconut.
Place flat side down on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill until chocolate is set, about 10 minutes.

title: extra moist applesauce cake
directions: Combine butter, applesauce and raisins in 3-quart pan.
Heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat and add soda (will foam up). Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry bacon and crumble; cook onion in grease until clear.
Mix beans and other ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Simmer over low flame for 15 minutes or put in crock-pot.

title: granny apple squash
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Half squash and scoop out seeds.
Rub cut surfaces and cavities with oil.
Put, flesh down, on a baking sheet or bake until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Scoop out flesh from squash.

title: south african deviled rock lobster
directions: Drop lobster tails into large kettle of boiling, salted water. When water reboils, begin counting time; boil for 5 minutes. Drain off water and drench in cold water.
Cut through undershell with scissors; remove meat and reserve shells.
Flake meat with a fork.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered 10 x 6 x 2
baking dish, sprinkle with cinnamon and salt. Add water. Rub together flour, sugar and margarine. Drop mixture over apples. Bake 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into pie shell.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on (last 10 minutes of baking) to form glazed top.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking pan, melt margarine/butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter evenly. Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chocolate and peanut butter chips and press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Cool; cut into bars and store covered at room temperature.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies well; mix with melted oleo.
Put this in bottom of cake pan for crust, saving some to sprinkle on top.
Cream the softened cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add 8 ounces of Cool Whip; put on top of crust.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture in pan.
Put in refrigerator and let stand for a few minutes.
Put layers of Cool Whip on top; sprinkle with rest of crushed Oreos.
Serves 10.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt. In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil and buttermilk; add vanilla. Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: nashville fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread into well-greased pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve warm with ice cream.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: Cut cabbage into quarters and remove core.
Slice cabbage into 1-inch slices.
Slice carrots and potatoes each into about 10 slices.
Put cabbage and vegetables into large pan and cover with cold water.
Bring to rapid boil for about 10 minutes so cabbage can settle.
Drain 1/3 of water.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper and oil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Then add rice and simmer 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.
Calories:
300 per serving.

title: garlic pesto chicken linguini(30 minutes or less!)
directions: Saute chicken breasts (cut into bite-size pieces) until done, in nonstick pan, in wine or broth.
Add garlic and mushrooms; cook for 4 more minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apples and sugar; stir nuts in last.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, combine ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir until ground beef is brown and onion and pepper are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: blini(russian yeast pancakes)
directions: Mix the yeast with enough warm water to form a smooth paste. Add the rest of the water and half the flour, sifted.
Mix with a wooden spoon; cover and leave in a warm place for about 30 minutes.
It should double in volume and be full of bubbles. Gradually add the rest of the sifted flour, beating until the mixture is smooth.
Stir in the melted butter, egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Warm the milk and add it gradually until a smooth batter is obtained.
Leave in a warm place to rise a second time. Beat the egg whites until they hold soft peaks and fold them in when the mixture has doubled.
Allow to rise a third time.
The batter should be full of bubbles.
Heat two small frying pans and brush them with melted butter or oil.
Pour tablespoons of batter into frying pans.
The blini should be thin and full of holes like lace.
Makes about 32 blini.

title: kart-wheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, oleo, powdered sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
(If dough seems dry, mix in more milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.) Divide the dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each part into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Make an indentation, 1 3/4-inches in diameter and about 3/4-inch deep, in center of each flattened ball.
Fill each indentation with about 2 tablespoons of pie filling.
Bake until edges begin to brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 "Kart-Wheels".

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together with spoon and spread into a greased, glass, rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, flour, oil and eggs. Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Do not overbake.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and sugar; add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add juice.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Add apples, celery, and nuts.
Put half in bowl; spread with 1/2 of soft cream cheese. Top with other half of jello mixture and spread with remaining cream cheese.
Chill until set.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef until slightly browned and drain.
Combine spaghetti sauce and water.
Spread 1/2 cup of sauce in a lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Arrange 4 uncooked lasagna noodles on sauce.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.
Spread 1/2 over noodles.
Layer with half each of Mozzarella cheese, remaining sauce and beef.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: pea pods with almonds
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and chicken bouillon. Set aside.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add almonds; stir-fry 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add frozen pea pods; stir-fry 2 minutes more.
Stir in mushrooms, drained.
Stir cornstarch mixture and add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, then cook and stir 2 minutes more.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and shake well.
Makes about 2/3 cup.

title: breakfast squares
directions: Cook sausage as you would for spaghetti.
When done, add cheese and melt.
Spread on bread and cut into half or quarter pieces. Put on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bread browns.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well, usually 8 to 10 minutes, as this is the secret to a fine grained cake.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and sour cream alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites with the salt beaten in.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato relish
directions: Put spice in cloth and tie up.
Mix all ingredients together and cook real low for 2 hours.

title: potato-peanut butter roll
directions: Boil potato in jacket until tender; peel and mash.
Add butter.
Sprinkle some powdered sugar on waxed paper.
Add rest of powdered sugar to potato.
Roll this mixture on waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Add peanut butter.
Roll and cut into pieces.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll pieces of beef stew meat in flour to coat. Heat the oil in a large nonstick pan over high heat. When the oil is hot, add about half of the meat and brown it on all sides for 3 minutes. Remove the pieces of meat with tongs and place them in a Dutch oven. Repeat this procedure with remaining meat; adding more olive oil as needed. Add hot water to meat and bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, reduce the heat to low, cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes(great for potluck dinners)
directions: Slice potatoes; parboil 10 minutes.
Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, cheese, soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush corn flakes.
Add 1/4 cup butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli with cheese
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Melt cheese with butter.
Crush 1 cylinder of crackers.
Alternate broccoli, cheese sauce and crackers in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sinful peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter over low heat until smooth. Add sugar and mix.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Cool 2 hours before cutting into pieces.

title: fat-free corn chowder
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute onion in margarine until tender and transparent.
In soup pot, cook potatoes in 4 cups water until done; do not drain.
Add onion and all remaining ingredients to pot.
Cook over low to medium heat 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
This tastes even better if made the night before.

title: dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, 2 sticks margarine and sugar.
Beat 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour sifted with baking powder, one spoonful at a time, alternately with 1/4 cup milk.
Add vanilla. Stir in crushed pineapple and juice and blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when touched.
Let stand for
a few minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup softened margarine, powdered sugar and 1 cup crushed pineapple.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: herb broiled tomatoes
directions: Mix herbs and bread crumbs and set aside.
Pour melted butter over tomato halves.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste and then with herb mixture. Finally sprinkle on grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes until cheese bubbles and browns.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: admiral angel food
directions: Cut angel food cake into small cubes; set aside.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add sour cream; mix.
Place a layer of cake cubes in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour part of pudding mixture over cake.
Next, add a layer of pie filling.
Repeat. Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: mayonnaise(my mother made this.)
directions: Stir together until thick as custard.
When cool, pour over cabbage.

title: crispy coated chicken
directions: Crush soup mix in pouch.
Combine soup mix, bread crumbs and pepper.
Beat together egg and water.
Dip chicken into egg mixture.
Coat with crumb mixture.

title: kay's breakfast egg casserole
directions: Butter bread
slices and place in a long casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Beat eggs and add half and half or milk and 1 teaspoon
salt;
set
aside.
Brown
sausage, drain and pour over bread
in
dish.
Add
1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese. Pour egg mixture
on top and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: waffles divine
directions: In 1-quart casserole, soften cheese in microwave.
Stir in soup until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir once during heating.
Garnish with chopped tomato.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Nuts, chocolate chips or raisins may be added to dough, also.
Bake at 350° or 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil raisins, water mixture and baking soda 2 minutes and let cool.
Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add raisin mixture, then add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Use 6 Number 2 tin cans greased and floured.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes, then at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix well at medium speed.
Bake in 325° oven.
Makes 2 long layers.
Frost with Pig Pickin Cake Frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and press all ingredients together and roll into ball. Sprinkle with paprika. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion, zucchini, yellow squash and peppers in 1 1/2 cups oil until soft (can use oil sparingly).
In skillet, saute eggplant in 1/2 cup oil (can decrease oil).
Add tomatoes, broth, parsley and spices.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add beans, chickpeas and corn; adjust seasonings.
Serve with grated Mozzarella cheese, sour cream and bread on the side.
Serves 12.

title: ann gratwick's vegetable souffle
directions: Thaw
spinach
and
drain.
Slice crusts from bread and cut each
slice
into
squares.
Place
bread
in buttered casserole, 13
x
9-inch. Beat eggs, milk and 1 teaspoon salt. Pour this
over
bread, allowing time for bread to soak up all liquid,
at
least
hour.
Arrange tomato wedges over bread evenly
and
pour
remaining tomato liquid over all.
Add salt and pepper
to
taste.
Mix
drained
spinach
with undiluted mushroom
soup
and spoon this mixture over tomatoes, allowing the tomatoes to show through. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about
1 hour or at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes if in a hurry. Serves 8.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Put enough blackberries in a large pan.
Mix enough sugar to sweeten.
Add cornstarch, salt and cinnamon. Mix well with berries.
Put into a prepared pie shell. Dot with butter.
Cover with crust with slits in it.
Bake about 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: chili stew
directions: Cook onion, garlic and pepper in bacon grease until tender. Push to one side and brown hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook beef. Add chopped onions and drain. Season with salt and pepper. Put beef and onion mixture in a saucepan. Add soups. NO water. Cut cheese into small squares and drop in saucepan. Cook on low. Cook noodles and drain. When cheese melts, pour over noodles and mix. Serve with rolls and a salad.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain kraut (wash if too
salty).
Add chopped onion, celery, bell pepper and chopped pimento.
Stir until well mixed.
Add sugar to vinegar; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over mixed vegetables; stir.
Cover and set overnight.
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 teaspoons sugar and butter. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside.

title: french toast
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over margarine.
Beat eggs and dip bread into egg to coat both sides.
Lay over sugar mixture.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds and veins from peppers and chop fine in the blender.
Can use some of vinegar to help chop in blender.
Mix all ingredients except Certo and food coloring.
Cook on low heat 45 minutes.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes, then add Certo and your choice of food coloring.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 7 half pints. May spread on cream cheese and serve on crackers.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables and/or potato chips.

title: pecan tassies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften at room temperature.
Blend together.
Stir in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: fudgy mint cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate with 1/2 cup margarine. In bowl, combine chocolate mixture with sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla and flour.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese, 2 tablespoons margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk then remaining ingredients.
Pour over brownie layer.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Top with glaze.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cinnamon swirl
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon. After all other ingredients are mixed, put sugar and cinnamon on top of cake and cut through the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple peanut butter bread
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Add peanut butter chips, nuts and raisins.
Combine egg and milk; stir into oat mixture.
Add applesauce.
Beat mixture vigorously by hand for 30 seconds.
Spoon into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Sprinkle chips on top. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thicken juice of large can of sliced pineapple with heaping tablespoonfuls of cornstarch.
Let this stand until ice cold. Whip the whipping cream; mix with thickened pineapple juice, then mix with the diced fruit.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Bring carrots to a boil; drain.
Add tomato soup; add other ingredients.
Marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: fruit with honey dip
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Prepare Honey Dip.
Toss banana slices in pineapple juice; drain.
Arrange fruit on a serving tray.
Serve with Honey Dip.
If ripe cantaloupe isn't available, use 3 tart apples and cut into slices.
Dip in pineapple juice.
Makes a good substitute.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms (about 5 1/2 cups).
In a large bowl, place greens.
Arrange onion rings, olives, radishes and reserved mushrooms on top of greens.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, thyme, garlic powder and black pepper; pour over salad just before serving.
Toss gently to coat completely.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Stir together sugar, salt, mustard, onion and half of the vinegar.
Gradually beat in vegetable oil.
Gradually stir in remaining vinegar and celery seed.
Makes about 2 quarts; keep refrigerated.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Add egg and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies will still be soft.
Cool on sheets until set, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: taco salad(microwave)
directions: Place ground beef in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook on full power for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until beef is no longer pink. Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.

title: rice, broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine first 3 ingredients and sprinkle over melted oleo. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry and line pie pan; set aside.
Cream butter with vanilla, then add sugar gradually; mix well.
Then add eggs in thirds, blending well after each addition.
Thoroughly blend in chopped pecans along with syrup and salt. Turn into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Arrange pecan halves over top of filling.
Continue baking 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: salsa
directions: May substitute juice from chilies for the vinegar and may add Tabasco sauce.

title: black walnut ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Then add 1 large can Borden cream. Mix again.
Pour in freezer can and add 1/2 gallon sweet milk. Freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a bowl, cream together the sugar, butter or shortening and eggs. Add pumpkin and juice. In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, allspice and cinnamon together. Add to first mixture.
Mix until blended.
Add nuts and dates.
Place in two greased loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until bread springs back at touch.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cut up bananas.
Put vanilla wafers in a bowl.
Boil all milk, sugar and eggs together until thick, then pour it in the bowl with the bananas and vanilla wafers.
Put in the refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins.
Chop up onion, celery, hard-cooked eggs and peeled potatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in dressing mix.
Place 1/3 dressing in baking dish, 1/2 chicken pieces, celery soup diluted with 1/2 can stock, another layer, 1/3 dressing mix, rest of chicken, chicken soup diluted with 1/2 can stock.
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add milk.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Toast nutmeats; add 1/2 cup to batter.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan; sprinkle with remaining nutmeats.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove cake from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: beef stew supreme
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, brown meat and onions in oil. Reduce heat to low.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl and sprinkle over meat mixture.
Add vinegar, catsup and boiling liquid.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours on low heat or until meat is tender.

title: cranberry jello relish
directions: Blend cranberries, almonds, orange rind and sugar in a food processor; then add orange juice.
Make up Jell-O.
When Jell-O begins to harden, add fruit mixture.

title: pumpkin cake(great for the thanksgiving holiday!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix together; make well in center of dry ingredients. Break in eggs; add oil and pumpkin.
Mix well with spoon.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(I've also used a Bundt pan.)

title: cherry dessert(this is so easy and good!)
directions: Put pie filling in a 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over the top.
Drizzle melted butter all over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Let cool 1 hour before serving.
Good warm or at room temperature.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 1 minute.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Bake in a 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and soda; add alternately to egg mixture with 1/2 cup lemonade concentrate. From a teaspoon drop dough 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
Brush hot cookies lightly with remaining lemonade concentrate; sprinkle with sugar.
Remove cookies to cooling rack.
Makes about 4 dozen small cookies.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start timing after mixture reaches a full, rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Stir until blended. Then drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls. Coconut or chopped dates may be added, if desired. These may be placed in the refrigerator to hasten hardening.

title: creamy cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely chop the cabbage and cook for 10 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan and add flour and stir until smooth.

Gradually add milk and cream and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add salt, pepper and nutmeg. Add cabbage to sauce and pour in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with buttered crumbs. Drizzle with melted butter and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: bay-leaf loaf
directions: Put gluten, nuts and onion through blender.
Add unbeaten eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add oil (less 1 tablespoon). Put in baking pan and top with bay leaves and 2/3 cup hot water. Combine the remaining 1 tablespoon oil and 1/3 cup hot water and use for basting while baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove the bay leaves just before serving.
Serve with desired gravy or cranberry sauce.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine rice, tomatoes, eggs and tuna.
In a small bowl, combine oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; pour over salad and stir until well mixed.
Chill.

title: crab goodies
directions: Halve the English muffins and set aside.
Mix by hand the remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Cut into quarters.
Place on baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 7 minutes and serve.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Crush blackberries, one layer at a time. Pour fruit into jelly bag and let juice drip. Measure sugar into separate bowl. Mix 1/4 cup sugar from measured amount to fruit pectin in a small bowl. Stir mixture into juice in saucepot. Add margarine. Bring mixture to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Quickly, add remaining sugar. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and skim off foam with metal spoon. Ladle into jars. Wipe rims and threads. Cover with two-piece lids. Screw bands tightly. Invert jars 5 minutes, then turn upright. After jars cool, check seals. Makes about 6 cups. Jelly takes up to 1 week to set.

title: grilled grouper with cantaloupe-lime salsa
directions: Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat) or preheat broiler.
Mix first 6 ingredients in nonaluminum bowl.
Season to taste with salt.
Let stand at room temperature at least 15 minutes or cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.
Brush fillets with oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grill fish until just cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.
Transfer fish to plates.
Spoon salsa over fish.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.	Grease baking sheet with shortening. Measure
into
mixing bowl first 5 ingredients.
Cream these ingredients
lightly;
then add flour.
Knead as you add flour. Roll your dough in a ball, pinch off small amounts and pat flat on	baking	sheet.	Cook about 10 or 15 minutes.
Do not overcook. Makes 24 cookies.

title: poor folk's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and place a large iron skillet with margarine in oven.
When margarine is melted, add 1 pie crust and return to oven until crispy and slightly brown.
(You may turn on broiler to speed up process.)

title: fried corn
directions: In large skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add corn, onion bits, salt and pepper.
Stir until lightly brown.
Add cream cheese and mix until cheese is melted or well blended.

title: aunt lila's glazed popcorn
directions: In a big shallow pan, put margarine, brown sugar and Karo; cook on slow fire; boil 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and beat. Pour mixture over popcorn (popped) and pecans and stir well.
Cook in low oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and oil slowly.
Beat for 3 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and butter hard for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cling wrap.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour. Boil mixed vegetables until tender.
Separate chicken after cooling in greased Pyrex dish.
Drain vegetables.
Then spread vegetables over chicken, onion salt and pepper.
Mix 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and 1 1/4 cups of broth.
Spread over chicken and vegetables.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Line an oblong pan with aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper meat. Place meat in the pan.
Combine all of the ingredients and put on top of the meat.
Cover with foil and cook in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple strudel
directions: Mix ingredients together with enough flour so it is not sticky (not
too
hard).
Let
set for some time as it gives. This is enough for two strudels.

title: my mom's macaroni & cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bring to a boil a large pot of slightly salted water. Add pasta and cook 8-10 minutes or until tender. Drain. Place macaroni in a 2 qt. dish. Stir in cheese soup and milk until well combined. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake 25-30 minutes until cheese is brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat thawed strawberries and jello until jello is dissolved. Mix milk and vanilla pudding mix.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer ingredients, starting with vanilla wafers, strawberry mixture and pudding mixture. Top with wafers and garnish with Cool Whip and fresh strawberries.

title: onion potato bake
directions: Place in plastic bag.
Shake very well coating potatoes.
Then empty into a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak bran and sour milk together.
May add nuts, raisins or dates.
Bake at 325° in convection oven for 25 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: sausage stuffed thighs
directions: Saute sausages in skillet 5 minutes, turning once.
Open thighs flat, sprinkle with equal amounts of salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Place 1 sausage in center of each thigh and roll up. Dust each thigh with flour and, holding thigh together with sausage inside, carefully dip in eggs and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in baking pan in preheated 350° oven.
Bake 1 hour.

title: four-layer dessert(variations: pecan delight, lemon lush, cherry delight)
directions: Combine flour, melted butter and half of nuts. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° until lightly browned. Cool.

title: apple hassie cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Add molasses and water.
Cook until apples are tender.
Beat oil, sugar and egg, then add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Pour all liquid of apples. Add milk to make 1 cup of liquid; add to batter.
Fold in apples. Sprinkle topping on before baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chantilly chicken
directions: Blend sour cream and apricot jam together.
Spread over chicken in roasting pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake slowly at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until rosy and tender.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown beef and onion while cooking noodles as package directs. Drain noodles and stir into beef mixture.
Add seasonings and all but a small amount of grated cheese and stir.
Place in a greased casserole and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Pop into a 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crunch cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients well in large mixing bowl.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: boomer chili
directions: Simmer beef broth, peeled red onion and seeded chili peppers for one hour.
Remove onion and peppers and finely chop them.
In a large pot melt the Crisco and saute the garlic, onion and peppers.
Cut the beef into 1/2 inch squares and add them to the pot.
Cook them over medium heat until they are gray.
Add the salt, oregano, cumi, chili pepper, black pepper and paprika and stir together for about 2 minutes.
Add the beef broth and simmer over low for 2 hours.
Stir in masa flour and cook for another 20 minutes.
Serve when at the proper thickness.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Pound beef slices to flatten and tenderize.
Mix egg and milk in pie pan.
Dip meat slices in egg-milk mixture, then in crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar and flour.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add melted butter and mix.
Stir in milk.
Pour into buttered dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Stir after it has cooked 1/2 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and form meatballs. Roll in cracker meal; brown and drain on paper towel.

title: mixed fruit dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold into fruit mixture and chill thoroughly. Yields 6 servings.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel and slice apples, or leave peel on.
Melt margarine in a medium to large skillet over medium heat.
Add apple slices-fry until tender.
Add brown sugar, more or less depending on tartness.
Serve warm.

title: baked ham
directions: Place in pan, skin side up.
Heat 20 minutes.
Remove the skin, score the fat in diamonds.
Mix fruit and sugar together and spread evenly on ham.
Repeat spreading fruit and sugar each 10 minutes, until all is used.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat.
Cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until hot.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Place in casserole and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.
Can do ahead.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion.
Combine beaten egg with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by small spoonfuls into oil.
When done hushpuppies will float.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields:
36-48 small hush puppies.

title: pork `n' cabbage
directions: Brown meat.
Cover and cook 15 minutes; drain.
Stir in vegetables, water and Italian dressing.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce, combined with cornstarch.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Wonderfully different, with oriental twist.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix.
Pour into 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; turn into casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs in one tablespoon melted butter.
Brown in 350° oven until it bubbles and browns.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine unsifted dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into ungreased 12 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dumplins
directions: Pour broth and soup into boiler and bring to a	boil. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add a little butter. Break thawed dumplins into small pieces and add slowly, stirring as you add them. Stir very gently. Cook about 20 to 30 minutes or until dumplins are tender.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add 1 cup milk and butter.
In small mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and 1 cup milk and add to saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat until mixture is thick and starts to bubble.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into baked 9-inch pie crust.
Makes one pie.

title: double tomato bruschetta
directions: Preheat the broiler.
In large bowl, combine the tomatoes, sun dried tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper.
Allow the mixture to sit for 10 minutes.

title: democrat pie
directions: Blend ingredients together and fill graham crust.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spring peas and lettuce
directions: Cut lettuce into small strips.
Saute onions and garlic about 1 to 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add lettuce and saute 1 minute. Add peas, salt and pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Serve warm.

title: yummy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with frozen ice ring decorated with strawberries.
Makes 30 (5 ounce) servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into brownie squares.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper; drain.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain off liquid; add eggs and milk.
In large baking dish, layer 1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 hamburger, 1/2 pepperoni and 1/2 sauce; repeat layers.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake.
Poke holes in the cake when it is slightly cool. Dribble the condensed milk and the caramel sauce.
Let set for 1 hour.
Put Cool Whip on top and then the crushed Heath bars.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix egg yolk, salt, paprika and lemon juice or vinegar.
Beat together as olive oil is added, a little at a time, until the whole is consistency of cream.
This should make a cup of dressing.

title: sourdough muffins and coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle this mixture over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, coconut and any optional ingredients you prefer.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet or roll dough into rolls.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated 2 to 3 weeks or frozen for 3 months.

title: egg dumpling
directions: Stir briskly to make soft dough.
Drop by 1/4 tsp. into boiling soup.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes. Makes 3 pies.

title: amish cake
directions: Stir soda into buttermilk to dissolve.
Combine 1 stick oleo, brown sugar, buttermilk/soda, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.
Spread topping consisting of the last 4 ingredients over top of cake and return to oven until topping is bubbly.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Put roast on rack.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 325 degrees for 40 minutes per pound.
Cool and slice thin.
Save drippings.
Add rest of ingredients to drippings.
Simmer 30 minutes and cool.
Add to sliced beef.
Let sit 4-5 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, heat gently but do not boil.

title: japanese fruit piefrom north carolina
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add the beaten eggs.
Beat well and add the vanilla.
Add the rest of the ingredients, and pour into an unbaked pie shell (9 inches).

title: holly berry punch
directions: Combine juices, water and grenadine syrup; mix well. Add ginger ale just before serving. Pour over ice in punch bowl. Float slices of lemon or orange for garnish. Yields 2 3/4 quarts.

title: "fantastic" company chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in bite-size chunks.
Saute in frying pan with Worcestershire sauce until done.
Salt and pepper to taste. Layer bottom of 9 x 13 Pyrex dish with chicken.
Cook bag of veggies as directed; drain.
Combine veggies, sliced potatoes, mushroom soup, 1/2 bag Cheddar, 1/2 can onion rings, mushrooms and sour cream; mix all together.
Then spread mixture evenly over chicken in dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle rest of cheese and onion rings over dish.
Return to oven to melt cheese and brown onion rings.
Serve with fruit salad.
Fantastic.

title: grilled raw potatoes
directions: We usually make this to serve two.
You can adjust the amounts for larger groups.

title: mashed potato nests
directions: Cook potatoes; mash until smooth. Add butter, seasonings and hot milk, beating until light and fluffy.
Make 6 mounds of mashed potatoes in a buttered, shallow baking pan.
Shape into nests with spoon and fluff edges with a fork.
Fill centers with well seasoned peas and carrots.
Place under broiler until edges of potatoes are hot and lightly browned.

title: fried plantation (ecuadorian meal)
directions: Cut plantations (wedged cut); place in skillet of hot olive oil.
Cook until brown on high or medium heat.
When browned and tender, place sugar in Zippy bag and place the cooked plantation in; shake well.
When cool, ready to serve.
Ecuadorian favorite dish.

title: apple cinnamon flaps
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients and stir into dry until moistened.
Cook on hot griddle (350°).
Makes 15 pancakes. Heart healthy.

title: soft spicy hermits
directions: Cream salad oil and sugar.
Sift 3 cups flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add molasses and milk alternately with flour mixture and 3/4 cup raisins and walnuts.
Spread in a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When taken out of oven, sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine soups and rice.
Place chicken on top.
Pour over melted butter.
Sprinkle package of Lipton onion soup on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients and store in sealed container.
Add 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
asparagus,	and mix well. Spoon
over
asparagus
spears and chill before serving. If desired, you may garnish with pimento strips, tomato wedges or hard-boiled egg slices.

title: mama's biscuit pudding
directions: In a saucepan dissolve sugar in milk and water over low heat. Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add biscuit crumbs, butter,
egg and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baking dish and bake
at
until
firm,
about 1 hour.
May add raisins, if desired.
Light bread crumbs may be used.

title: jello punch
directions: Heat 1 pint of water to boiling and dissolve Jell-O in it. Heat another pint of water to boiling.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let set.
Add sugar to tea.
Add pineapple juice, lemonade, Jell-O and rest of water (3 quarts).
Stir well and chill.

title: fettuccine with artichokes
directions: Cook fettuccine according to directions.
Keep warm.
Mix together the butter and cream on low heat.
Add artichokes, salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese. Toss with pasta and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Serve immediately.

title: refried beans
directions: Heat frying pan.
Add oil or lard.
Heat well.
Pour in leftover beans and bean liquid.
Be prepared for sizzling and spattering!
Let beans sizzle and simmer.
Mash with a spoon or masher as they cook.
They don't have to be perfectly mashed. Great for burritos.

title: poppy seed loaves
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, seed, water and oil all at once in large mixer bowl on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Spread in 2 to 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Make a glaze of the powdered sugar and lemon juice and spread over the loaves while they are still warm.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended but don't beat.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 80 minutes or until cake tests done.
Test after 60 minutes as that is all it takes in my oven. Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove and serve plain or with confectioners sugar sprinkled on top.
Cake will remain fresh and moist if refrigerated.

title: good luck black-eyed pea soup
directions: In large stockpot, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes. Add broth, tomatoes, peas, water, ham and thyme.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Add oleo, sugar and raisins. Take off heat.
Add milk and vanilla to well beaten eggs.
Pour over rice mixture and stir well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: polish mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Can be refrigerated up to 2 days.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and beef casserole
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with one slice of bacon.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chipped beef.
Combine mushrooms and soup; pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 3 hours.

title: poor man's beans
directions: Open beans with can opener.
Put spoon into beans and eat!

title: charlie's caesar salad
directions: Break garlic into large wooden salad bowl.
Add vinegar and lemon juice; soak for 2 hours.
Drink wine.
Remove garlic from liquid and rub sides of bowl.
Dice half of 1 clove and leave in liquid.
Add egg, olive oil and anchovy paste.
Tear romaine into 1-inch squares.
Toss with croutons; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: carolina ham in gingersnap sauce
directions: Broil ham for about 15 minutes, turning often.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cook on moderate heat until smooth.
Serve on ham.

title: whipped banana yogurt(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine orange juice and orange peel in small saucepan; cook and stir over medium heat until peel is tender.
Let cool; refrigerate.
Combine banana pieces and lemon juice in mixing bowl or food processor; whip to puree.
Add orange juice; mix together. Add yogurt; whip just to blend.
Pour into a 8-inch round cake pan; freeze until firm.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add beaten eggs, then hot water. Add flour mixed with soda.
Add nuts, oats and vanilla; then the butterscotch morsels.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Grease spring pan.
Spread graham cracker crumb crust in bottom, pack down.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off and let cake cool in oven for at least 2 hours.

title: seafoam
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until syrup cracks when dropped from teaspoon in cold water (about 262° on candy thermometer).
Pour slowly into beaten egg whites and beat until desired firmness. You will have to beat the last with a spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Flavorings or nuts may be added during the final beating.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix by hand in large bowl.
Por in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator bran rolls
directions: In the 1 cup boiling water, stir Crisco until melted. Add sugar and salt; stir to dissolve. Last add All-Bran. In the 1 cup warm water, dissolve yeast. Sift flour and measure out 6 cups. Beat the eggs. When lukewarm, place first mixture in a large mixing bowl. Add yeast mixture and eggs.
Add flour, a little at a time. Grease another large mixing bowl and place dough in it overnight, covered, in refrigerator.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In medium mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, egg, shortening and approximately 1/2 of the flour.
Beat with spoon until smooth. Mix in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Let rise in greased bowl, covered until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again until doubled.
Shape into rolls; brush with melted butter and cover.
