Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake 12 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.

title: fried squash
directions: Pare and cut the squash into thin slices.
Dip slices in crumbs, then in beaten egg, then in more crumbs.
Fry in deep fat (395°) from 4 to 5 minutes.
When the slices are brown, drain them on soft paper.
Serve on a flat platter or dish.
(Fried squash makes an excellent luncheon dish.)

title: texas cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Brown sausage and pour off grease.
Pour broth over bread crumbs and let soften.
Mix other ingredients with bread crumbs.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stove-top chicken and rice
directions: *For a milder flavor, can substitute Italian-style stewed tomatoes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In blender or small bowl, combine all ingredients until smooth. Cover and refrigerate.
It tastes better after being refrigerated overnight.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and pecans; set aside. In another bowl, combine melted butter and beaten eggs; mix well. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Fill greased and floured mini muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for about 15 to 16 minutes. Do not overbake. Remove immediately to wire rack to cool. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: christmas toffee
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 325°. Spread out almonds on a baking sheet and bake, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, 5-7 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pork amandine
directions: Place each tenderloin piece between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and gently press to 1/8-inch thickness.
Set aside.

title: frosty peach punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: dressing for potato salad
directions: Beat eggs well and add milk and cornstarch.
Boil vinegar, sugar and butter.
Add half of mixture to eggs and milk, then pour in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Makes dressing for 4 or 5 potatoes.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Wash, then soak beans overnight.
Boil beans until edges curl when blown on.
Place beans and bean water in a large crock.
Add salt pork, molasses, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Bury onions, after pricking with a fork, in the beans.
Add enough water to cover beans.
Bake, covered, at 225° to 250° for 8 to 9 hours or overnight.

title: noel cookies
directions: Blend butter, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add flour.
Beat egg whites.
Roll dough into balls.
Dip in egg whites.
Roll in pecans.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool on a rack.
Mix 1 cup confectioners sugar with food coloring.
Moisten with milk.
Ice cookies on top.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Mop top of biscuits with butter as soon as removed from oven.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir together the oats, sugar, wheat germ, nuts, coconut bran and seeds.
In a small pan, heat the oil, honey and vanilla until bubbling.
Thoroughly mix liquids with dry ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Stir until cool.
Add raisins when cool.
Makes about 15 cups.

title: veal patties(kalve karbonader)
directions: Beat eggs and cream together slightly.
Crush and grind zwieback into fine crumbs and add to cream.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Gradually add zwieback mixture to meat.
Form into round cakes, 2 inches in diameter.
Cook in butter over low heat until patties are cooked through, turning once.
Yield:
about 12 patties.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the margarine or soft shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips and nuts. Chill.
Then drop by rounded teaspoonfuls apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 375°.
Remember, cookies continue to bake on a hot cookie sheet even if removed from oven.

title: curried peas and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter; add flour and mix until blended.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add seasonings, peas and mushrooms.
Cook until hot.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Break up ground beef; put in bottom of 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with onions and add Tater Tots.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Cube chicken and brown in skillet.
Add rice, black beans, and water.
Cook until rice is done.
Add corn and salsa.
Cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on dish and top with cheese, sour cream. Put nacho chips on the side.
You can add more salsa if dry or top with other favorite toppings.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos (with icing) and mix with oleo.
Set aside 1/2 cup.
Spread rest of cookie mixture in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Cook pudding and let stand for 5 minutes.
Pour over Oreo crust and put in refrigerator until firm.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Oreo mix that you set aside.
Chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch or flour, cocoa, egg and milk; stir well.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly until thick. Makes 2 pies.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken (stewed and removed from bone), chicken soup (undiluted), Chinese vegetables (drained), mayonnaise, water chestnuts (drained) and 1/2 Chinese noodles.
Mix well.
Place in a baking dish.
Garnish with remaining noodles.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: melon salad
directions: Combine lemon jello and 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Add cold ginger ale and chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Meanwhile, cut into balls with melon cutter.
Fold into mixture with peaches and grapes.
Chill until firm.

title: oven crusty fish
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Dip the fish into the egg mixture.
Coat generously with corn flake crumbs.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serve with lemon wedges dipped into finely chopped parsley.

title: corn moxcheux
directions: Cut
corn
off	cob
and
scrape
the cob.
Add corn to heated oil in heavy pan, cook on medium high, adding a little water
if needed.
Add
onions,
bell
peppers,
tomatoes and garlic, stirring frequently.
Cook for about 8 to 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 2 hours on low, stirring often.

title: pinto beans in pressure cooker
directions: Put the beans in pressure cooker with all ingredients.
Cook with pressure up for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix together ground beef, oats, 1 cup chopped onion, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder, eggs, condensed milk, salt and pepper. Shape into balls and put in 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Drain.

title: white tex mex chili
directions: Boil chicken and separate into small pieces.
Saute onion and garlic; then add chilies and tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in skillet; and let simmer for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and crisco.
Add sugar and beat until creamy. Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla.

title: venison burgers
directions: Combine ingredients and form into patties.
Cook in skillet with small amount of oil over medium heat until done.

title: peach salad
directions: Arrange on flat plate the canned peach halves.
Place in center of each 1 tablespoon finely chopped walnuts.
Over this put 2 teaspoons marshmallow cream, then sprinkle with grated coconut. Top with a cherry.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oysters in juice while preparing sauce by browning butter, adding flour then milk.
In 2 quart casserole place layer of oysters, then sauce, then 1/2 of crumbs.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Over all pour 1 cup of liquid from oysters.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom and up sides a little). Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar, a little at a time until mixed.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Add 2 - 4 tablespoons of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet; brown the lamb shanks on all sides. Transfer to a 2 1/2-quart glass or ceramic casserole.
Stir the flour into the oil.
Add the beef broth gradually, stirring to a smooth sauce.
Add all the remaining ingredients, except the peas. Pour over the lamb.
Cover and cook on "Roast" setting for 50 minutes.
Add the peas; continue cooking for 10 minutes at the same setting.
Yields 4 servings.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter and flour; mix well. Add milk slowly. Cook until thick. Add salt and pepper.

title: tijuana train wreck
directions: Heat 2
tablespoons olive or regular oil. Add onion and garlic;
saute.
Add
ground
beef;
brown.
Drain grease off. Add other
ingredients.
Let simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Can cook and serve
in
crock-pot.
Serve
with
Doritos
chips, diced tomato, shredded
lettuce, grated cheese, olives, sour cream, chopped onions,
avocado, etc.
Place crushed chips on plate, then sauce, then toppings of choice.
Nice for parties.

title: green beans
directions: Fry cut up bacon with onion.
Add flour, sugar and cut up tomatoes; thicken.
Put beans in casserole; add other ingredients. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
In bowl, combine other ingredients until crumbly. Spread over apples and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves six.

title: lazy day pierogi
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Meanwhile, partially cook noodles. Drain and mix with onions and butter.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Slice margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute seafood and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients gradually, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Heat to boiling.
Serve at once with croutons or crackers.

title: anise drop cookies
directions: Beat eggs 15 minutes.
Gradually add sugar and beat; add flour and continue beating.
Add salt and baking powder and beat.
Space anise seed (4 to 7) on 5 cookie sheets (disposables work fine) and drop dough by teaspoonfuls, approximately 30 per sheet.
Allow to stand overnight.
Do not pile pans on top of each other, they must lie flat.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, dates and beaten egg.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes until dates are fine.
Remove from stove; add Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts.
Let cool.
Roll and shape.
Roll in fine coconut.

title: best rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, bring rice and 1 quart milk to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring often, for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: pecan potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, put whole sweet potatoes and water to cover and cook until done.
Remove potatoes and, when cool enough, peel them and mash well, creaming in nutmeg; spoon mixture into a baking dish.
In a skillet, melt the oleo; add sugar and pecans and cook until sugar is dissolved; pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate
in
water over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add
sugar
and salt.
Cook and stir until smooth and slightly thick.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: corny chocolate crunch
directions: Combine 1-3/4 cups all-purpose flour with 3/4 cup confectioners sugar; cut in 3/4 cup cold butter or margarine.
Press firmly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese supreme
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix all other ingredients while macaroni is cooking.
When macaroni is tender, drain and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly beat in sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Carefully fold in nuts and crackers.
Bake in greased 10-inch pie plate at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool. Good plain or with coffee or vanilla ice cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour milk over bread; let it soak until it falls apart.
Mix in egg, spices and Worcestershire; mix well.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix in meat.
Spread in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Drain off grease after cooked.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients in roaster.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook, drain and chill macaroni.
Add all remaining ingredients, then toss with macaroni.
Good sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: pork chops with sauerkraut
directions: In skillet brown pork chops.
Put sauerkraut in casserole. When chops are browned, drain drippings into sauerkraut.
Add tomato paste.
Place chops on top.
Add water, salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 1 hour in oven at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast to water.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add salt, lukewarm water and oil.
Beat on low speed.
Add yeast; mix with spatula.
Add flour, not making too sticky or stiff.
Let rise in a warm place.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out the next day and bake.

title: snickers apple salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add diced apples and Snickers.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: "applewoods" apple fritters
directions: Mix fruit, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir until just moist; put in airtight bowl. Heat oil in deep fryer or pan 350°, drop in dough and cook until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Let cool about 15 minutes. Add soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and pimento.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Grease casserole dish.
Melt butter; pour over herb dressing.
Line bottom of dish with dressing, top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken enchiladas(great for leftover turkey or chicken)
directions: Combine in saucepan and heat thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Dip tortillas in hot oil until soft.
Combine the cheese and onion in a bowl.
Put 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture in center of tortilla.
Roll tortilla and put in baking dish. Pour turkey sauce over tortillas.
Cover with foil for oven at 350° for 25 minutes, or cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: german style green beans
directions: Saute bacon in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until crisp. Add chopped onion; saute until tender.
Add bouillon granules, pepper and flour to bacon and onion and mix well.
Increase heat to medium.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Add liquid to bacon mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Put beans in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour bacon mixture over green beans. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Store in covered container to mellow.

title: lemon slices
directions: Mix slightly beaten eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Mix baking powder and flour and add to egg mixture.
Spread on warm layer as soon as you take it out of the oven and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Can be sprinkled with powdered sugar or left plain.
Cut into bars when cool.
Freezes well with wax paper in between layers.

title: fudge
directions: Chill about 1 hour.

title: frozen fruitcake salad
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients, fold in fruit and nuts. Turn into 4-1/2 c. ring mold.
Freeze several hours or overnight. Unmold on lettuce lined plate, garnish with additional cherries. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: emerald punch
directions: Combine concentrates (I use blender).
Pour into punch bowl. Add 7-Up.
Stir gently.

title: microwave sweet pickles
directions: In small bowl or measuring pitcher, combine salt, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, vinegar and sugar.
Mix cucumbers and onions in microwave-safe bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power 5 minutes.
Stir well. Return to microwave 5 minutes more.
Cool. Pour into quart jar and refrigerate.
Pickles are ready to eat when thoroughly chilled.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: make ahead cocktail cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball and sprinkle with parsley.
Press parsley gently into cheese ball.
Wrap cheese ball in heavy-duty plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter cornflake treats
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat.
Heat and stir just until well blended.
Remove from heat. Add corn flakes and mix well. Pour into square cake pan.
Press down with hands.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature. Heat oven to 325°. With hands, combine sausage and cheese together in a bowl. Add Bix-Mix and blend thoroughly. Roll into little marble size balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold. Makes about 60 balls.

title: almost-homemade lemonade
directions: Mix in 1/2 gallon container.
Add water to fill container. Mix and serve.

title: taco beef
directions: Cook beef for 5 minutes.
Add taco seasoning.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Add stewed tomatoes, beans and liquid. Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked, drained egg noodles.

title: no-cook mint patties
directions: Thoroughly blend butter, corn syrup, extract and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar; mix with spoon and hands until blended smooth.
Divide mixture into thirds.
Knead red coloring into one portion of mixture and green coloring into another, leaving one portion white.
Shape into round balls; flatten with tines of fork on wax paper lined baking sheets.
Let dry several hours.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: bean and frank cup
directions: Place each biscuit into the bottom and up the sides of each greased muffin cup.
Cut hot dogs into thin slices.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix soft butter, onion, dry mustard, poppy seed and Beau Monde together.
Slice Italian or French bread in half lengthwise. Spread butter mixture on both halves.
Top 1/2 with Swiss cheese (bottom).
Place top on bottom half.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes (ovens may vary), wrapped in foil.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.
Slice and serve.
Serves approximately 10 to 12 people.
Great for parties or family get togethers.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots for 5 minutes; drain and cool.
In medium bowl, put salt, pepper and mustard.
Beat in a little of the oil to blend with mustard.
Add the remainder of the oil, sugar, vinegar and soup.
Beat until mixed.
Add onion, peppers and carrots. Cover tightly and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of milk and flour. Add extract.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rich macaroni-n-cheese
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Cook low 3 minutes.
Gradually add milk with whip.
Cook until just boiling.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add pepper and hot sauce.
Add cream; simmer 1 minute.
Add 3/4 cheese.
Stir; heat over low until melted.
Mix mac into cheese sauce.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Top remaining cheese and bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; refrigerate overnight. When ready to bake, place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not cover.
Bake for approximately 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Holds well for serving.
Serves 12.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomato in slices 1/2-inch thick.
Mix flour and 1/2 of sugar.
Sprinkle on both sides of the slices the remaining sugar and salt.
Dip the slices in the flour and sugar mixture.
Let stand for 5 minutes and dip again.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over butter/margarine.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: linda's "creamy conch on pasta"
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add garlic and shallots, saute until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and increase heat.
Gently boil wine until reduced by half, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add cream and simmer until thick and reduced by half, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in conch.
Simmer until
heated through.
The heat will cook the conch, if you leave it, but its usually more tender if you just heat it through.
Season to taste with parsley, salt, and pepper.
Serve over pasta.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly and slice very thin.
Mix above ingredients and let stand in plastic or glass containers in refrigerator.
Ready to eat in one day.

title: short ribs
directions: Place short ribs in large pan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 2 hours.
Drain off water, saving 1 cup. Mix remaining ingredients; add to meat and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: Heat milk, butter and sugar until dissolved.
Stir in 25 marshmallows.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add 2 ounces unsweetened chocolate, Hershey chocolate bar with almonds and chocolate chips.
Pour in 3 pie pans, buttered well. Refrigerate until firm.
Use a big pan and stir a lot!

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the flour, nuts and butter together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend 1 cup Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Put cream cheese mixture on top of cooled crust.
Beat the lemon pudding and milk until thick and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large bowl.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and melt.
Cool.
Add
water to get proper consistency.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla and butter; bring to a boil for 2 minutes and turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, stir until melted. Add all chocolate and stir until melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine and blend. Pour into 1 deep-dish pie shell or 2 regular. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside and let cool.
Mix salad dressing and mustard. Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except macaroni). Add salad dressing mixture.
Add macaroni.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour vinegar mixture over salad and mix well.
Put in a sealed container and refrigerate.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sour cream and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda and beat well, only long enough to mix well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peach supreme pie
directions: Mix pecans, brown sugar, flour and margarine together.
Place into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake until brown.
Let cool.
Mix together the confectioners sugar, the Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over cooled crust.
Next, spread 1 can of peach pie filling over the top.

title: swiss baked fish fillets
directions: Arrange fish fillets in lightly greased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking pan.
In small bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Spread mixture over fish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: micro peanut brittle
directions: Stir; cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir; cook 4 minutes more.
Add 1 tablespoon oleo and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend well.
Return to microwave.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda. Stir fast.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stuffed zucchini(serves two)
directions: Wash zucchini; cut off ends and halve lengthwise.
Drop into pot of boiling water and cook until slightly tender.
Plunge zucchini into cold water, allow to cool, then drain.
Scoop out pulp with a spoon, leaving shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Drain shells on paper towels.

title: hash brown scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream and flour mixture, beating to blend thoroughly.
Spoon batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle topping over top and with a knife or rubber spatula, cut topping through cake to give a marbling effect.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: johnny knows it all
directions: Cook chopped onion, pepper and celery together in a small amount of butter.
Add meat and cook until slightly browned. Drain.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water and drain.

title: ring of fire(cheese spread)
directions: Grease a jello ring with butter; put 1/2 cup of pecans in bottom of mold.
Mix all ingredients, except pecans, well and press half of the mixture in mold.
Put the remaining pecans on top of this.
Press remainder of the cheese mixture on pecans. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove and turn out on plate.
Fill center with ripe olives and place crackers around ring.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Chop onion, green pepper, tomatoes and celery stalks.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Heat soup, enchilada sauce, green chilies and water.
Line bottom of pan with crushed Doritos.
Add layers of meat, cheese and soup mixture.
Let stand a few minutes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit; reserve juice.
Take up to 3 cups juice and cook with both pudding mixes until thick.
(Can do in microwave.)
Chill.

title: chinese sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and soy sauce in a cup.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and bring to simmer; add cornstarch mixture and simmer until it thickens and clears, stirring constantly.
If too thick, thin with a little pineapple juice.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Lightly brown 1 pie crust on top and side using broiler.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour berries in crust.
Put mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Combine margarine and cheese; blend until smooth.
Add flour and hot sauce; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stop.
Stir well. Return to oven and microwave on High 4 minutes more.
Stop.
Stir in margarine.
Microwave 2 minutes longer on High.
Stir in vanilla.
Add baking soda.
Quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour out onto a lightly greased baking sheet or dish. Spread to about 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
In blender, process remaining ingredients on medium speed until combined; add flour mixture and process on low speed until smooth.
Set four 6 ounce custard cups on baking sheet; place in oven for 5 minutes.
Spray each with nonstick spray and pour 1/4 of batter into each cup.
Return to oven and bake for 20 minutes. Turn oven control to 325° and bake 20 minutes more.
Remove popovers from cups.
Serve immediately.
Popovers will fall slightly after removing from oven.

title: chicken and broccoli supreme
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Cut into bite size pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli for 3 minutes.

Mix next 4 ingredients, using only 1 cup cheese. Line 2-quart baking dish with chicken; layer broccoli on top. Pour sauce over broccoli. Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over cheese. Bake 45 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add in eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and dry ingredients alternating with milk.
Fold in berries.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix oil, eggs, vanilla, water and brown sugar; blend well. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add pecans; mix well. Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with large package semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese-dill dip
directions: In a blender, combine cottage cheese, green onion, snipped parsley, dill weed, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and garlic powder. Cover and blend until smooth.
Chill for at least one hour before serving.

title: chi chi
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze at least 24 hours. Do not mix while in freezer.
Can be mixed with 7-Up.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix together cocoa, cornstarch, salt, sugar, egg yolks and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir constantly.
Add flavoring and pour into a pie crust.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together sauerkraut and sugar and let stand for at least 1 hour.
Add celery, carrot and onion.
Add pimento and green pepper (optional).

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie shell in 450° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble in pie shell.
Add cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until almost set in center.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: pecan sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Add flour mixture, slowly.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
Make each into a log and roll on wax paper.
Roll up in the paper and put in freezer for a couple hours or fridge overnight.
Slice and bake 9 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool on brown paper.

title: celtic chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper and pound until thin.
In a medium bowl, mix together the egg, soy sauce, Irish Mist and garlic.
Place chicken in mixture; turn to coat. Let stand 1 hour.
Coat each chicken breast with bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, heat butter and oil.
Fry cutlets 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until crusty and brown.
Drain on absorbent paper. Serve on a bed of wild rice with lemon and capers.

title: chicken a l'orange 1
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Spray a cold, large, nonstick skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken in hot skillet for 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink, turning once.
Meanwhile, for sauce, in a small saucepan, stir together the cornstarch, orange peel and salt.
Gradually stir the 1/2 cup orange juice into the cornstarch mixture.
Stir in the orange liqueur and honey.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Stir in the orange sections; heat through.

title: chicken and chips casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup and milk.
Set aside while you prepare the other ingredients. Melt butter in a saucepan and add celery and onion; cook over low heat until transparent.
Remove from heat and stir in peas and chicken.
Add this mixture to the rice/soup mixture and mix well. Layer 1 1/2 cups crushed chips in the bottom of a buttered casserole dish.
Carefully pour in the chicken mixture.
Top with remainder of chips.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until chips have turned rich brown.
Serve piping hot.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and salt on medium heat.
Boil about 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and color.
Mix and pour over popcorn.
Shape into balls with buttered hands.

title: garlic veggie casserole
directions: Saute minced garlic and broccoli until veggie loses crispness. Add the rest of ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
This recipe is also good with cauliflower and Swiss cheese.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease three round layer pans, 8 or 9-inches.
Line with wax paper.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Combine the next 4.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan (oiled and floured).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Bring water to a boil; add salt.
Remove from heat.
Add alum, oil and food coloring.
Mix in flour.
Knead until smooth.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: whole wheat pizza dough
directions: Thoroughly mix undissolved yeast with 1/3 of flour and all other dry ingredients.
Heat liquids with shortening over low heat until very warm.
(Shortening does not need to melt.)
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beaten eggs.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour.
Refrigerate. Shape dough and let rise until twice in size.
Bake at 450° for pizza for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Roll out rolls onto a cookie sheet and press "seams" together. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread on baked crust.
Top with any or all of the following chopped fine vegetables: broccoli, carrots, onions, green pepper, celery, radishes, green or black olives, mushrooms or cauliflower.
Put in refrigerator and let stand for 24 hours before serving.
Remove and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave one-step lasagna
directions: Crumble beef (ground turkey can be substitute for half the beef) into skillet and saute until no longer pink.
Combine meat, spaghetti sauce, water and wine.
Spread 1/3 of sauce mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwaveable baking dish. Arrange 4 lasagna noodles on sauce.
Layer 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Spoon half of remaining sauce over cheese.
Top with 4 lasagna noodles and 1 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap. Fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape. Microwave at Medium (50% power) 32 to 35 minutes, giving dish a half-turn after 15 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and microwave at Medium for 2 minutes. Before serving, garnish with green pepper rings, if desired.
Let stand for at least 5 minutes before serving, so that it will thicken.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and Fritos.
Line casserole dish with Fritos.
Pour half of meat mixture over Fritos and then 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Repeat with last of meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large pot over medium gas until it comes to slow boil.
Turn gas to simmer for about 35 minutes.
Turn off gas. Combine in a bowl the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add mixture to pot and stir well. Add the raisins.
Pour in a baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover and let cool.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir hot water in gradually.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Slowly stir half the hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth. Blend in butter and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue.
Bake at 400° until delicately brown.

title: lipton toasty onion sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Trim crusts from bread.
Spread Onion Butter on bread slices.
Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Place strips on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen sticks.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, hot water.
Heat slowly until sugar is dissolved.
Boil without stirring to firm ball stage (248°). Gradually beat hot syrup into stiff egg whites.
Add salt and vanilla.
Cool.
Fold in mayonnaise and orange peel.
Serve as dressing for strawberries, fruit salad or any fresh fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, sugar and the 2 tablespoons of flour and spread in a greased baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, oats and 1/2 cup flour and spread over apples.
Drip melted butter over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream. Cinnamon may be sprinkled on the apples, if desired.

title: teriyaki pork chops
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce, brown sugar, green onion and lemon juice.
Marinate pork chops in mixture.
Set in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.
Place chops in broiler pan.
Broil 6 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil and buttermilk. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in vanilla, carrots, raisins, pineapple, walnuts and coconut; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup of milk on low temperature and set aside.
Mix cake mixture, oleo and 3/4 cup milk well.
Bake 1/2 of cake mixture for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take 1/2 cake from the oven.
Spread caramels, chips and pecans on top.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake for 15 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pork chops jamaica
directions: Brown chops in frying pan.
Remove to shallow roasting pan. Add broth and bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: glazed lamb chops
directions: Rub chops with cut garlic clove.
Brown chops in skillet, turning frequently.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Uncover; turn chops and cook until sauce thickens.
Yields 2 servings.

title: granola supreme
directions: In a large bowl, mix together whole wheat flour, corn meal, wheat germ, rolled oats, brown sugar, powdered milk, coconut, cinnamon, walnuts, almonds and cashews.
In blender, add the honey, oil, water, salt and vanilla.
On low speed, puree until blended.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients and mix well. Spread on large baking sheets.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Bake until light brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Add dried fruits such as:
raisins, dates, dried apples or dried apricots, if desired.
Store in a sealed container.
Yields approximately 7 1/2 pounds.

title: italian bread dressing
directions: Mix together and add sage and poultry seasoning to taste.
Add a small amount of chicken broth.
If too thick, add 1 package of dry vegetable soup mix and cook at 325° until done.
Stir often.

title: toasted cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 3 - 4 logs.
Bake at 350° for 20 mins.
Slice and bake again on both sides 10 mins or more until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar together until sugar is dissolved. Pour over other ingredients.
Stir well.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut meat into 2-inch cubes.
Peel and halve carrots.
Quarter celery stalks.
Cut onion in eighths.
Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven with tight cover.
Cook in 300° oven for 4 hours. Do not uncover while cooking.
Pan may be covered with foil under the cover to insure tightness.
Serves 6 generously.

title: rainbow salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Dissolve jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Add 1/2 c. cold water.
Add apple and refrigerate.

title: last minute punch
directions: Let punch set for a few minutes with the sherbet in it so it will get slightly creamy.

title: barbecue chicken white sauce
directions: Place thawed thicken in large container with top.
Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl and pour over top of chicken, saving some for basting for safety reasons.
Let chicken marinate 24 hours and then cook and baste.
Umm!
Umm!

title: easy peach cream pie
directions: Place peaches in pie shell.
Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in cream and vanilla; blend well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center shakes slightly when moves.
Serve warm or for a firmer pie, chill before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 2 nights, then add sliced beef.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and olives
directions: Mix and stir tomato paste, tomato puree, olives and juice. Add chicken and enough water to cover chicken. Cook on top of stove for 1 hour.
Serve it with dumplings.

title: microwave caramel corn(filer township aux.)
directions: Pop the popcorn and place in large heavy paper bag.
Place remaining ingredients in 4-cup Pyrex measuring cup.
Bring to boil on High in microwave (takes about 2 minutes).
Boil for 2 minutes on High, watch so it doesn't boil over.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir until foaming.
Pour over popcorn and shake well. Cook another 1 1/2 minutes and shake bag.
Cook 30 seconds and shake well.
Cook another 30 seconds.
Cool in bag.
When cool, break it up.
Store in covered container.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Pour a little tomato sauce into bottom of pan.
Spread evenly. Add rest of tomato sauce to meat.
Add oats, cheese, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into ball.

title: artichoke antipasto
directions: Drain artichokes.
Cut in bite size pieces. Drain olives. Drain peppers and cut in strips. Cut cheese in squares.
Cut salami in strips.
If too long, cut in half.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Season with oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic salt. (Don't use too much oil and vinegar.)

title: buenos nachos
directions: Combine sour cream and guacamole until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto serving platter; top with chips. Combine Velveeta, milk and onions in saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Cover chips with cheese spread mixture; top with tomatoes and olives.

title: festive cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with pecans.
Mix thoroughly, but do not beat.
Spoon into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Let cool completely before frosting.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Put Carnation milk into large bowl.
Put into freezer until almost frozen.
Congeal jello, juice of one lemon, 1 1/2 cups hot water and 3/4 cup sugar.
Whip milk until fluffy; add jello mix. Crush Nabisco wafers, putting half on bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Add jello mixture.
Top with remaining wafers. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Can be cut into serving sizes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Top with 1 roll Ritz crackers, finely crumbled and mixed with 2/3 cup melted butter. Bake for 25 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, sour cream, milk and 2 cups whipped topping in bowl.
Beat until blended.
Spoon 1/2 the filling into crust.
Arrange berries in filling and press down.
Top with remaining filling.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and additional strawberries, if desired.

title: old fashion chicken pie
directions: Note:
With
the
fat
content	of today's poultry, you probably won't need the butter except in the crusts.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until easily removed from bones.
Debone and chop meat.
You will need at least 2 cups of poultry.
Pour water and all remaining ingredients into large Dutch oven or pan. Bring to boil, then simmer until all vegetables are cooked.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Chop eggs, onions, celery and pepper quite fine.
Mix all together with dressing and let stand in refrigerator overnight or for several hours.

title: shoe peg corn pea salad
directions: Combine in saucepan and bring to a boil the first 6 ingredients.
Cool.
Combine all other ingredients and pour cooled vinegar over all.
Chill overnight.
Makes sizable amount.

title: ham ball
directions: Set cream cheese out to get soft.
Slice ham into little strips.
Slice onions into small circles.

title: spicy mango salad
directions: Combine mango, red pepper and onion strips in a large bowl; set aside.
Cut poblano chili pepper into quarters; remove seeds and membranes.
Cut into thin strips; add to mango mixture.
Add green onions and remaining ingredients, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill.
Yields 5 cups.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 baking pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Slice carrots.
Simmer in small amount of water and salt for about 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter. Stir in brown sugar over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add carrots.
Cook for 10 minutes, turning and stirring often.
Serve hot.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until margarine melts.
Serve warm over ice cream. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening together.
Add the flour, soda, salt mixture, unbeaten eggs and vanilla alternately to the creamed ingredients.
Add nuts.
Form into loaves.
Shape cookies anyway you want (round, square, oblong).
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake at 325° to 350° about 12 minutes until brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and eat!

title: party cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Crush bouillon cubes in water and add gradually to cheese, mixing well until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with assorted crisp chips and raw vegetable sticks.
If dip is not to be served immediately, refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: ketchup
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add 1 cup corn starch, mixed with cold water.
Cook another 1/2 hour.
Can in hot jars.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together.
Heat 2 packages flour tortillas (steam to flex). Spread thin layer of mixture on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice and serve with picante sauce.

title: shredded apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into unbaked pie shell. Cut remaining pastry into strips and place crisscrossed across top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together and shape into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together well.
Add olives and chives.
Stir together well.
Chill slightly (about 1 hour).
Form into a ball.
Chill again (about 2 hours).
Roll ball in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts until all are pressed in.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Serve with assorted crackers and/or chips.
You can make smaller balls if you wish and want more nuts.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, cooking oil, sugar, dry mustard, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Arrange in bean pot: layer of cabbage and layer of onion.
Repeat until all used.
Top with sugar.

title: creamed corn bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 8-inch square pan.
Mix Bisquick, egg and creamed corn together.
Pour in hot pan.
Do not stir in butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly; cut and serve.

title: rice krispies and cheese
directions: Mix together.
Make roll.
Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: citrus crown cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch bundt pan.

title: tropical fruit bread
directions: Cream sugar and
shortening.
Mix
in
eggs thoroughly. Combine bananas and buttermilk.
Blend dry ingredients and add alternately with banana
mixture
to creamed mixture.
Stir in bran, apricots and nuts.
Bake about 60 minutes in loaf pans.

title: cocoa party cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and cocoa in a medium bowl.
Blend well. Add milk.
Beat with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Fold in thawed topping.
Spoon into baked and cooled crust.
Freeze at least 4 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef with onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Drain. Combine eggs and cottage cheese. Set aside. In baking dish, pour some of the Ragu sauce on bottom, then layer spaghetti, ground beef and cheese mixture. Repeat layers. Top with sauce. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Combine soups, milk and broth or water. Heat thoroughly. Combine stuffing mix and melted butter. Spread half of stuffing in a greased 9
X 13 pan. Layer chicken over this and pour soup mixture over. Top with the remaining stuffing. Bake uncovered about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix together, form ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: delicate bleaching
directions: Instead of scouring and scrubbing the rings and burner drip pans of your range, place them in a large plastic bag.
Add 1 cup ammonia, full strength; close and secure tightly.
Let them set for an hour or more.
Wash with warm water.
Dried grease will rinse off.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix together and pour in a 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to your ice cream maker directions.

title: rolled peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together.
Roll out thin. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll in long rolls and slice.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Put egg mixture in apples and sugar.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare cake mix as per instructions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk in sauce pan over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Pour over cake

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil, garlic, salt, pepper and ginger.
Saute steak in mixture until brown.
Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Simmer 15 minutes until green peppers are tender.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Add to meat mixture stirring until thick.
This makes the gravy.
If too thick, add 1/4 cup water.
Serve over rice.

title: cookies 'n cream
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; add milk and syrup.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Set aside until well cooled.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and add cookies.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for 1 hour.
Soften the ice cream; spread over the cookie mixture.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Pour the syrup mixture over ice cream.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip over syrup.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: turkey loaf
directions: One hundred extra calories a day:
1 tablespoon butter or 1 (2-inch) biscuit or 1 scoop ice cream, can add up to 10 extra pounds in one year.

title: angel eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs; cut in half.
Remove yolks and set shells aside.
Smash yolks with fork; add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth and creamy.
Fill shells with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix steak with flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown in oil.
In a roasting pan mix soup, onion soup mix and the milk. Add steak.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook and drain the noodles.
Mix in the sour cream.
Pour the beef mixture over the top and serve.

title: honey-mustard dressing(serve over raw spinach)
directions: Heat vinegar and honey in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring until honey dissolves.
Pour into bowl and cool.
Whisk in mayonnaise, mustard, onion and parsley.
Gradually whisk in oil.
Pour into a jar and refrigerate.
Can be prepared 3 days ahead.
Bring to room temperature and shake well before using. Serve over raw spinach.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, mustard, egg and bread crumbs; mix and add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Knead together until well mixed.
Form into loaf and put in oven pan. Top with ketchup as to taste.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: country casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3 qt. baking dish. Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 60 minutes.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix and pour over potatoes.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Scramble hamburger and mix with the potatoes.
Stir in soup and mix well.
Put mix in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with shredded Colby cheese (or any cheese).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine and mix well:
cake mix, margarine, water, oil and 1/2 can of Eagle Brand.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt and mix together the caramels and remaining 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk. Spread over the baked layer.
Sprinkle generously with chopped pecans.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes longer.
Frost.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine the 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and the stick of melted margarine and spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat the 2 sticks softened margarine, confectioners sugar and eggs no less than 15 minutes. Spread over crust. Cover with bananas, strawberries and pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over fruit and sprinkle nuts on top. Refrigerate overnight. Cut into squares to serve.

title: german upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put pecans in bottom. Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour batter over pecans.
Cream the butter and cream cheese; mix well.
Add powdered sugar and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over uncooked cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: marinated tomatoes and onion
directions: Arrange tomatoes in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar, cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over tomato slices. Cover and refrigerate several hours or quick chill in freezer.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 can of soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour remainder of soup over loaf.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in large pan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in cheese and milk.
Stir over medium heat until soup simmers and thickens slightly.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle servings with paprika.
Enjoy!

title: berry cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, sour cream and milk in mixing bowl and whisk for 1 minute.
Spoon half into pie shell.
Top with berries.
Cover with remaining pudding.
Frost with Cool Whip. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: penuche nuts
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar with cream and stir well over low heat until sugars
are dissolved.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute or until all sugar crystals on sides of pan have melted.
Remove cover and cook until a ball (little harder than a soft ball) forms when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until mixture begins to cover nuts.
Turn on waxed paper (sprayed with Pam) and separate nuts. "Store in airtight container."

title: brandy alexander pie
directions: In a saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Stir.
Heat and stir until thick.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and add cognac and creme de cacao. Chill until the mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon. Beat egg whites until stiff; add remaining sugar and fold into mixture.
Fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Turn into crust; chill. Garnish with remaining whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: strawberry banana smoothie
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth and serve immediately.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm, not hot, water using spoon.
Add remaining ingredients as listed.
Grease muffin pans; fill about half full with batter.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Batter can be kept in refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: impossible french pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean. Frost with Red Velvet Cake Icing.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine all other ingredients and cook until beans are tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Spread chilies out in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chilies.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: easy lime pie
directions: Combine limeade and milk.
Add sour cream; stir until well blended.
Fold in Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Add food coloring. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Garnish with chocolate chips, if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and potatoes.
Cook beans and potatoes, covered, on low heat, until oleo melts.
Stir beans and potatoes.
Cover with oleo.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Top with one can of fried onion rings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the breakfast sausage and drain off grease in colander. Cube the bread and place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.

title: shrimp butter spread
directions: Mix together; form into a ball. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: swiss apple pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vanilla and beat again.
Sift dry ingredients together; add egg mixture.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with ice cream and whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a greased baking dish, place asparagus.
Cover with canned soup and crushed crackers.
Pour milk over top.
Top with cheese and sliced eggs.

title: kahlua
directions: Pour boiling water over coffee and sugar.
Stir, chill before adding vodka and vanilla.
Pour into gallon jug.
Shake well before using.

title: vegetable shrimp stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet or wok, heat peanut oil over medium-high heat. Add snow peas, green onions and red pepper; stir and fry for 2 minutes. Add shrimp; continue cooking for 2 more minutes. Add mushrooms; stir-fry until tender and liquid evaporates. Add soy sauce, vinegar and sesame oil; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly. Serve over hot cooked white rice.

title: southern fried dove
directions: In a large cast iron skillet, add 1-inch of oil.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot (drop of water placed in oil sizzles; oil should not smoke). Dip breasts in egg and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour. Add dove breasts to skillet a few at a time and fry to a golden brown on all sides over medium-high heat. Don't overcrowd the skillet.

title: chocolate pastry twists
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pastry for two crust pie as directed on package.
Stir in sugar.
Roll into rectangle, 12 x 10-inch.
Spread with softened margarine.
Sprinkle with chocolate shots.

Cut pastry lengthwise with sharp knife into 20 (1/2-inch) strips. Cut each crosswise into 3 (4-inch) strips. Twist each strip several times. Place 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press ends onto sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 60 twists.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
Place pie pan on cookie sheet in case it boils over.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk together in blender.
Chop up wafers and layer on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then pour pudding on top of wafers.
Finally put a layer of whipped cream on top of pudding. Refrigerate to cool, about 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water; let partly jell. Add remaining ingredients.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients and put in freezer (stir several times during freezing).
Take out of freezer a couple hours before serving.
Don't thaw completely, leave a little "Chunky." Add fine chopped nuts and coconut to the above mixture and use at Christmas.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Make small balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: delicious bars
directions: Bake brownies on cookie sheet.
While warm, spread a small jar of marshmallow cream on top.
Let set for a short while.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread on top of brownies.

title: cheeseburger skillet supper
directions: Brown meat and celery in skillet.
Stir in tomatoes and gravy mix.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Before serving, top with cheese.
May be served over noodles, toast or toasted hamburger buns.
Can be doubled to serve 8 to 10.

title: patio beans
directions: In a 9 x 13 baking dish, combine beans, bacon, onion, cheese, brown sugar and ketchup.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until mixture bubbles.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare
potatoes;
cut
into
squares.
Combine
flour, cheese, salt
and pepper in a bag. Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in a bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt
butter
in
a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or dish. Place
potatoes
in
a
layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for about
1 hour, turning once during baking.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.

title: cold water cocoa cake
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks, one at a time, until well blended.
Sift flour, salt, cocoa and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the water.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat to stiff peaks.
Fold into batter.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Simmer giblets and neck in chicken broth until tender, about 2 hours.
Chop giblets into broth; discard neck.
Add onion, celery, poultry seasoning and dressing.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.
If a thicker gray is desired, add more dressing.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cut 2 tablespoons peanut butter into powdered sugar.
Sprinkle half powdered sugar in bottom of crust.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 tablespoon peanut butter and milk.
Mix and add Cool Whip and blend.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with rest of confectioners sugar. Chill or freeze.

title: low-fat chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. On each chicken fillet, place a slice of cheese and a slice of ham.
Roll fillet.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve the zucchini.
Scoop out centers leaving 1/4-inch shell. Place in shallow baking dish.
Coarsely chop zucchini centers. Mix with next eight ingredients.
Spoon into shells.
Top with spaghetti sauce or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves four.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil.
Mix until light yellow.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture.
This will be very stiff.
Add vanilla, stirring until well mixed.
Add apples and pecans, mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix whipped topping, pudding and pineapple with juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients; keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: veggie bar
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on baking sheet.
Press down and bake until light brown.
Cool.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add garlic, onion and parsley and cook until well blended.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste and equal amounts of water and boil 15 minutes.
Add spices, stir well and cook 3 to 4 hours.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking, uncovered, until very thick.

title: no fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and mix with peanut butter and vanilla.
Slowly add powdered sugar and cocoa, mixing as you add.
Mix well and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: country crust white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Stir together sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add to yeast. Mix in remaining flour. Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl; turn with greased side up. Let rise until doubled; punch down. Divide in 1/2. Roll out each 18 x 9-inch rectangle.

Roll up beginning at short side. Press together; seal. Place in greased pan (9 x 5 x 3); brush with oil. Let rise about 1 hour. Bake lowest rack in oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is brown. Brush with butter.

title: black forest pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar and cocoa, mix well. Add egg and almond extract. Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and refrigerate. Just before serving, top with cool whip, then pie filling.

title: tuna crunch(delicious microwave recipe)
directions: Combine celery, onion and butter in a 1-quart microproof casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Drain tuna and flake with fork.
Add tuna, soup, 2/3 can of noodles and cashews to onion mixture.
Stir carefully.
Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 2 minutes.
Stir mixture lightly.
Top with remaining noodles.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: Mix berries, rhubarb, sugar and water in a square pan; cook for 5 minutes. Measure flour. Mix flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar. Stir in oil and milk only until ingredients are moistened. Drop by spoonful on hot fruit; makes 9 `biscuits.' Make hole in top of each, putting a `dab' butter, sugar and cinnamon in each.

title: chicken baked in soup
directions: Put chicken in an oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and onions.
Combine undiluted soups with wine and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 2 hours at 350°.
May be prepared a day in advance, baking the next day.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip tomato slices in the mixture and coat with flour.
Fry in deep fat or pan-fry until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together until tender.
Drain well. Mix in rest of ingredients, except almonds.
Put in casserole dish, which has been lightly greased with margarine (or Pam).
Top with sliced almonds and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: almond-cheddar ball
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese together until smoothly blended.
Add pickle, sherry, mayonnaise, mustard and pepper; mix well.
Cover and chill until firm enough to handle.
Spread the nuts in a shallow baking pan and toast in a 350° oven for 8 minutes or until evenly browned.
Divide cheese mixture in half; shape each into a ball.
Wrap airtight and refrigerate as long as 2 weeks. Before serving, roll in almonds to coat evenly and let stand at room temperature about half an hour.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 balls, each about 4 inches in diameter.

title: grilled ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Slice ham, cheese and onion.
Spread margarine on one side only of each piece of bread.
Assemble onto a medium-high heated griddle in this order:
bread (margarine side down), Cheddar cheese, onion, ham, Swiss cheese, bread (margarine side up).
Grill until lightly browned.
Turn over and grill until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low.
Turn sandwiches again and cover with your biggest lid. Cook until medium brown and turn again.
Finish cooking, covered, until last side is medium-brown.
Remove from heat.
Slice in half and serve.
Serves 4.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add salt, baking soda and flour and mix well.
Stir in oats and Rice Krispies.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Add in and saute 1 large onion and garlic.
Add to this tomato sauce, soup and stewed tomatoes, celery and remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour. Serve over spaghetti.

title: sugar-free dessert
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and apricots and use to make pudding, plus 1 teaspoon lemon juice.

title: double corn soup
directions: Melt 4 ounces butter; add flour.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Bring quart of stock to a boil.
Remove from heat and gradually add flour to thicken mixture.
Saute shallots and pimentos in remaining butter.
Add corn and remaining stock.
Cook until tender.
Add thickened stock.
Simmer for 1/2 hour over low heat. Add cream and chicken meat.
Season and garnish.

title: shrimp fajitas
directions: Mix oil, lime juice, oregano, cumin and garlic in shallow glass or plastic dish.
Stir in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: walter's sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and oil and beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and pour half of the cake in pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake in pan. Pour remaining batter over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Make glaze by melting margarine, powdered sugar and enough milk for glaze consistency.
Pour over cake.
Best to use a tube pan for this cake.

title: frozen mint dessert
directions: In a large bowl, pour condensed milk, mint extract, 12 drops green food coloring and Cool Whip.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into dessert dishes and freeze overnight.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and let set.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Beat margarine until creamy.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add oats, mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together, add to oat mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pour on topping and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except macaroni and chips, in saucepan.
While heating through, boil macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Mix macaroni and sauce together. Pour into greased ovenproof bowl or microwave bowl.
Heat in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add potato chips to top for 5 more minutes at 325°.
Microwave for approximately 10 minutes, then top with potato chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mushroom-broccoli alfredo
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook broccoli, mushrooms, onion and garlic in hot margarine until vegetables are tender-crisp and liquid is evaporated, stirring often. Stir in soup, milk or wine, Parmesan cheese and black pepper.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over fettucine. Garnish with celery leaves.
Makes about 3 cups sauce or 4 servings.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion, green pepper, etc.
Mix all together.
Cook over medium heat 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir often. Serve on open hamburger buns.

title: pecan breakfast bread
directions: Preheat oven 375 degrees.
Unroll crescent rolls and separate into 16 triangles.
Spread with 2 Tbsp. softened butter.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Sprinkle over triangles.
Roll each triangle starting from wide end and rolling to opposite point. Place rolls point side down in greased 9 inch x 5 inch loaf pan forming two layers of
eight rolls each.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes until deep golden brown.
Remove from pan at once, place right side up and drizzle with topping.
Topping:
In saucepan, combine honey, confectioners sugar, 2 Tbsp. butter, and vanilla.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pecans and cool slightly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes in unbaked pie shell.
I make 2 pies from this recipe.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk. Bring mixture to a boil, and boil for at least 1 minute. Remove from the burner, and
add the remaining ingredients. Drop from a spoon onto waxed paper. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with soda; add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot sauce recipe
directions: Blend together.
Cook on low heat until mixture begins to boil.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: fluffy white rice
directions: Place rice, salt, water and butter in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, then turn heat to very low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
This recipe will make from 8 to 10 servings.

title: layered lemon cream dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs and walnuts, setting aside 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Make crust in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 5 minutes in a 350° oven and cool.

title: brisket
directions: Mix Coca-Cola, chili sauce and soup mix.
Place brisket, fat side up, in a Dutch oven or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture over Brisket and cover tightly with lid or foil. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes per pound, about 3 hours, or until tender.
Trim off fat after cooking.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Put ingredients into ice cream freezer.
Freeze.
May put a few chopped cherries in for color.

title: butterscotch toffee squares
directions: Spread first 6 ingredients in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with butterscotch and chocolate morsels.
When melted, spread like frosting.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Place pudding mix in bottom of large bowl to cover and add layer of vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Continue alternating layers: pudding, wafers and bananas; ending with pudding mix as top layer.
Place in refrigerator for 6 hours before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut
round steak in serving size pieces.
Sprinkle both sides of	steak with garlic salt and flour.
Pound flour into meat
with meat
hammer
or with sharp knife.
Fry in hot fat until brown on both sides.
Put meat into baking dish.
In the pan you
fried the meat, add 1 can tomato soup, 2 cups tomato juice
and
onion; cook until all the drippings of the pan are in the gravy.
Pour gravy over the meat and bake at 350° for 1 hour, reduce to 325° and bake until tender.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cheese torte
directions: Mix together; line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon ginger chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind and salt.
Pour over chicken, green grapes and celery; mix.
Sprinkle salad with toasted salted almonds and serve chilled.

title: farm style oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, lard, buttermilk and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten cookies with glass dipped in water to 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: cheese surprises
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Cut cheese into 20 even cubes.
Cut each biscuit in half and fold each half around a cube of cheese, pinching edges together.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 6 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with juice, marshmallows and nuts, if desired.
Sprinkle dry instant pudding on mixture.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: layered bacon salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Seal with mayonnaise. Cover with cheese.
Keep covered 6 to 12 hours in fridge.
Take out and mix up before serving!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread.
Add the peanuts.
Cook until a golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 heaping teaspoonful soda.
Stir and pour on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In saucepan, combine tomatoes, soup, broth and onion. Cover and bring to a boil; simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan. Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over corn and mix well.
