Spread on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring once to coat with syrup.
Spread out on counter from 10 to 15 minutes to cool.

title: red pepper soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine peppers, water, bouillon and Italian seasoning.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer over medium-low heat for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Put in blender to puree.
Add buttermilk and blend.
Return to saucepan and heat but do not boil or cover.
Serve hot or cold.

title: warm apple drink
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Stir 1/2 cup brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Keep warm in tea kettle on stove.

title: frozen banana dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir very well and pour into a 9-inch square dish or pan.
Freeze until firmly set.
Cut into squares and serve.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fried oysters without oysters
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease or oil.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: graham cracker crisps
directions: Mix butter, margarine and sugar in a double boiler; place over heat and bring to a boil.
Let boil slowly for 3 to 6 minutes. Line cookie sheet with foil; place graham crackers (broken at dividing lines) on cookie sheet and sprinkle with pecans.
Pour the cooked mixture over the crackers and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes at 325°.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Coat bottom and sides of a large roasting pan with vegetable spray.
Place popped popcorn in roasting pan.
In a heavy pan, slowly melt margarine; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool completely. Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: jamaican fricasseed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 12 pieces.
Wash and drain.
Add the onion, tomato, sweet pepper, salt, black pepper, m.s.g. and garlic powder.
Work ingredients into the chicken flesh, then leave to marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Scrape off the vegetables and retain them.
Fry chicken in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Strain off 1/3 cup of remaining oil, then wash the frying pan.
Heat the oil, add the marinade vegetables and remaining ingredients, including the chicken.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Mix the dry cake mix with the lemon pie filling.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with lemon frosting.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together and add 3 packages Equal sweetener and 1/2 cup Kraft Free dressing.
Sprinkle black pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
Chill for 1 hour and serve.
You may double this for a larger salad.

title: broccoli soup
directions: *May use 2 cups skim milk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini and flour sifted with cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cool for 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Blend together last five ingredients.
Heat wok.
Add peanut oil and brown beef.
Add pepper, scallions, onions and celery. Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stir-frying.
Stir in molasses mixture. Blend together 1/2 cup water and 2 tablespoons cornstarch and quickly stir in.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: white wine biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Mix together wine and oil.
Mix together the flour and liquid mixtures.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Sprinkle cabbage and salt and let stand 1/2 hour.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and pepper.
Bring to a boil, pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate; drain before serving.

title: cookie clusters
directions: Melt white chocolate wafers with peanut butter (do not allow to boil).
Let cool slightly and then stir in cereal and peanuts. Fold in marshmallows, then drop mixture by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool at least 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and finish filling a gallon container with water.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 3 cups boiling water. Chill slightly until thickened a bit.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a shallow pan and refrigerate.

title: homemade marshmallows
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of water and the four gelatin packets in a large bowl of an electric mixer with a whisk attachment.
Using a spoon, stir to combine,
but don't worry if the gelatin does not dissolve.
In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, light corn syrup, salt and another 3/4 cup water.
Stir well and bring to a boil over high heat.
Be careful, eventually the mixture will foam up and it's very hot!
Clip a candy thermometer to the side of the pan and cook until the mixture reaches 240° F.
Start the mixer on low speed and carefully add the hot syrup to the gelatin mixture. When the syrup is incorporated, increase the mixer speed to high. I use a Kitchen Aid.
They're notorious for over beating, so I turned it up to only 8 out of 10.
Leave the mixer running for 20 to 30 minutes.
The mixture will increase in volume and eventually reach the stiff peak stage.
It will start to look jagged around the edges of the mixer bowl.
While the mixer is running, brush a 9 x 13 inch pan with vegetable oil.
When the mixture reaches stiff peaks, add the vanilla and mix well.
Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and smooth with an offset spatula.
Let sit out overnight, uncovered (away from the cats and kids).
When you are ready to cut the marshmallows, dust the top with confectioner's sugar.
Use a sharp knife or a good pair of kitchen shears, the kind that come apart for thorough cleaning. Cut the marshmallows into manageable squares.
How big is manageable?
They're easier to eat if you pop the whole thing into your mouth, so run a test and see what works for you.
Dust or roll the marshmallows in more confectioner's sugar.
Or you can put two or three in a bag with sugar and shake them, making sure they don't stick together. Store them in tins with wax paper between the layers.

title: chau-chau
directions: Celery or cabbage may be substituted for cauliflower.
Chop fine.
Let stand overnight in brine made of salt in 5 quarts water.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the shrimp in a large skillet in the butter and oil for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove shrimp from pan and add flour on low heat.
Stir flour-butter mixture until lightly browned, then add onions, bell pepper and celery.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato saue, water, thyme, bay leaves, chili powder, sugar, garlic, salt, lemon slices and both peppers.
Stir well, cover pot and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add shallots, parsley and put shrimp back in.
Let it set for at least another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Combine top three ingredients and chill overnight.
The next day, add all or a combination of any of the chopped vegetables. Mix and it's ready to serve!

title: hot dog chow
directions: In a skillet chop hot dogs, onions, pepper and corn; fry until tender and hot dogs are hot.
Add 1 can tomatoes into hot mixture, until hot.
Add water and macaroni.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is done (15 minutes).
Serve with corn chips.

title: chinatown chicken simmer
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice. Mix 1/4 cup juice with cornstarch. Brown chicken well in oil; sprinkle with salt. Add garlic, onion and ginger; saute. Mix remaining juice with remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken. Cover; simmer 30 minutes. Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices. Cook until sauce boils. Add pineapple; heat through. Serves 4.

title: poppy seed walnut cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat thoroughly the sugar, oil, eggs and flavoring.
(Use vanilla with the pecans.)
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to mixture alternately with the evaporated milk, beating well after each addition.
Save about a tablespoon of flour mixture; coat nuts.
Beat in poppy seed filling; mix in the nuts mixed with a tablespoon of flour.
Place in ungreased 10-inch tube pan with solid bottom and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Invert cake pan and let cool completely before removing from pan.
Serve plain or sprinkled with confectioners sugar.

title: crab crostini
directions: Preheat broiler.
Line a broiler pan with foil.
Pick over crab meat to remove any cartilage.
In medium bowl, combine the crab meat, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, Parmesan cheese and hot pepper sauce and blend well.
Spread 1 tablespoon of the crab mixture on each slice of bread.
Place the crostini on broiler pan and broil 4-inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly brown.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: a tasty bug
directions: Here's what you need to make a ladybug.

title: grandma's brown sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add flour mixture and blend well.
Let dough rest 1/2 hour.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir or mix well the sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Mix well; add peanuts.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Mix well and add oleo and vanilla.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Mix rice, soup, onion soup and water in oblong baking dish. Put chicken on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°
up to 2 hours.
Check for doneness of chicken and dryness of rice.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix flour and spices together.
Melt shortening in baking dish. Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, in the pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn the chicken and bake until thickest pieces are brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9 for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salty water as directed.
Drain and put back in pot.
Add butter to macaroni, then add whipped eggs and milk. Stir in cheese.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until liquid is firm, but not dry.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set mixture aside.

title: barbecups
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar to ground beef.
Separate biscuits and place a biscuit in a muffin cup.
Press dough up the sides of cups.
Spoon meat mixture into each biscuit.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: luscious fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: lit'l smokies appetizers
directions: Take with you a bag of tortilla chips.
Really good, people just love it and easy to make.
Enjoy.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Make into a casserole; add cheese to top.
Cook 30 minutes in oven.

title: one bowl coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Drop on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned. Remove immediately.

title: play dough
directions: Pour liquids over dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Knead to play dough consistency.
May be stored in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: pignoli cookies
directions: Crumble paste.
Add sugar, fold in egg whites and mix with hands.
Refrigerate dough for 2 hours.
Shape into balls and press and shape into crescents.
Roll in pignoli nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Let cool for awhile on cookie sheet or they will break.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients to hamburger and mix.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.
This may also be put in a crock-pot.
Bake on slow for about four hours.
Watch so beans do not get mushy.

title: dixie onions
directions: Combine.
Put over onions; stir and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually, then add egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to batter gradually with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in batter lightly. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: sand cups
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in food processor or in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into a clean sand pail; add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in whipped topping.
Gradually stir in 1 cup crushed wafers.
Top with remaining crushed wafers. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Decorate just before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and make 1 large loaf or 2 smaller ones and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whip, blend in sugar, flour, salt, extract and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven on cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in salt water until tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Soup should be thick and creamy.
Thin with milk if necessary.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix black-eyed peas, tomato, green onions, garlic, green pepper and cilantro in a large bowl.
Gently stir in picante sauce, mixing well.
Add salt and pepper to taste; mix well. Cover and chill for 24 hours before serving.
This can also be served as an appetizer with tortillas or tortilla chips.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook
carrots,	drain
and
cool.
Chop onion and green pepper;
mix
all other ingredients in saucepan and heat until smooth
and sugar is melted.
Allow to cool, pour mixture over vegetables.
Cover	and
refrigerate.
Best
when marinated at least 12 hours.
Keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve sugar and cornstarch in water and salt.
Stir in Jell-O and stir until thick and bubbly; cool.
Put strawberries in pie shell; pour filling over and top with Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onion until soft.
Drain off water and add milk, butter, seasonings and parsley.
Let come to a boil.
Pour over toasted bread, broken into cubes and serve.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In a large bowl, combine mushroom soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and salt.
Add rice and chicken. Fold in broccoli.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with cheese and bake another 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: throwed rolls
directions: Combine sugar and yeast in tepid water. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until foamy. Mix milk, butter, sugar, egg and salt in large bowl. Stir in yeast mixture and 3 1/2 cups flour, adding a bit more to make soft, pliable dough. Turn dough onto floured board and let rest while you clean and butter bowl. Knead dough 4 to 5 minutes, adding flour if necessary. Return to bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise in warm place until double in size. Butter muffin tins. Punch down. Pinch off pieces to fill 1/2 of muffin cup and roll into ball. Put 2 balls into each cup. Cover loosely with plastic for 45 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Top with crushed corn flakes or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients.
Mix butter, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Add bananas then flour mixture, stirring well between additions.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: chicken-dressing bake
directions: Mix stuffing
mix
with 1/2 can of soup, chicken broth, beaten eggs,
onions
and	celery	seed.
Spread
mixture in a baking pan.
Top
with
cooked chicken.
Combine remaining 1/2 can of soup with milk and pimento.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue city chicken
directions: Spray bottom of 8-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Skewer city chicken on sticks and place in pan.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven until done (45 to 50 minutes). Serves 4.

title: toss salad
directions: Crumble in layers when cooled.
Let set overnight.
Add dressing and toss well.
Makes a very large bowl of salad.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease pan.
Mix well and bake at 400° until brown.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, apples and cinnamon.
Place in saucepan over low heat.
When juice forms, increase heat to medium.
Stir carefully occasionally until apples are done.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine flour, butter, grated cheese and sugar.
Crumble mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Cream the cheese at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°. Beat together the first five ingredients with mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Put cupcake liners in cupcake pans.
Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake liner (flat side down). Fill each liner 3/4 to the top with cheese filling.
Bake 20 minutes.
Let cool on rack and then top each cupcake with cherry pie filling.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients except milk for 15 minutes.
Pour into blender with the canned milk and blend a few minutes.
Cool.
It can be frozen.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Make a well and add salad oil, egg yolks and cold water.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl with cream of tartar.
Beat until very stiff peaks form.
Do not under beat!!! Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped egg whites, folding with rubber scraper.
Pour into 10 inch tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes in 325° oven.
Increase to 350 for 10 minutes.
If using 1/2 recipe, bake in 9 inch square pan, 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg salad mold
directions: Shell eggs and mash.
Add green pepper, pimiento, celery, parsley and onion.
Mash cheese; stir in mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Combine with vegetables and cooled, mashed eggs.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Chill 4 hours.
Serves 24.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs, oil, and buttermilk; stir in dry ingredients just until moistened. Gently fold in jam. Fill greased and paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375 for 20 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: almost heaven
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While still hot, prick with a fork and spread juice and crushed pineapple over top.
Let stand until cool or overnight.
Prepare the pudding as directed.
Add the cream cheese.
Spread over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, coconut or crushed candy.

title: delight supreme
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time until creamy.
Line bottom of 8 x 10-inch dish
with wafer crumbs and butter, saving 1 cup for top.
Spread sugar mixture over crumbs.
Layer fruit over sugar mixture.
Whip cream and spread over top.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: chiffon cocoa cake
directions: Mix cocoa and boiling water; set aside to cool.
Sift cake flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add in the following order: oil, egg yolks, cooled cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and set aside.
Beat egg whites until frothy in a large wide bowl.
Add cream of tartar and continue to beat slightly. Gradually add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, beating well after each addition.
Beat until rounded peaks are formed and whites do not slide when bowl is inverted.
Slowly pour yolk mixture over entire surface of whites.
Fold gently until completely blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Invert until cold.

title: mama's pork 'n' bean surprise
directions: Brown ground beef, cook onions with ground beef; drain.
Add pork 'n' beans, sugar and ketchup (if desired).
Mix together and simmer until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Pour boiling water on all ingredients in heatproof container. Cover.
Steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir and strain.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings; 2 calories each.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Drain chicken and break with fork.
Mix together with cream cheese.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans and parsley flakes. Serve with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cake mix and melted butter.
Beat until well blended.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix (dry) over top.
Drizzle 1 cup of chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken enchiladas are scrumptious
directions: Cube precooked chicken.
Add taco mix and stir.
Spread each tortilla with a layer of refried beans; spoon on about 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture and 1/4 cup or so Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up and place in a baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream together; spread over the top.
Sprinkle generously with remaining cheeses, green chilies and olives.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until enchiladas are bubbly.
Makes 12 enchiladas.

title: alberta salad
directions: Optional:
chopped celery, radishes, cucumber, bell peppers, or roasted sunflower seeds.

title: grilled corn
directions: Being careful to keep the husks on, clean, trim and remove the silks from as many ears of corn as you will need.
Straighten the husks.
Place the corn in a bowl and cover with cold water. Let it soak for 2 hours.
Take the corn out of the water and place over hot coals.
Roast until the husks are brown.
Husk and serve with salt, pepper and butter.

title: mince pie
directions: Mix mincemeat, apples, raisins and flavoring; pour into pie shell.
Cover with top pastry.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: boiled cookie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
While hot, add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: chick chick salad(6 servings)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the chicken, drained and rinsed garbanzos, green peas and 6 thinly sliced green onions.
Cover and refrigerate.
Peel, pit and slice avocados, then combine in a food processor or blender with oil, mayonnaise, yogurt, lime juice, salt, pepper, cumin and chili.
Process until smooth. Transfer dressing to a bowl; cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, combine the salad and dressing.
Garnish with remaining green onion, thinly sliced.

title: chocolate cake and chocolate frosting
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Mix well with mixer, then add the rest of the ingredients and mix as you go.
Add milk and flour together.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased and floured) and bake at 350°
for about 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix buttermilk, sugar, flour and butter together.
Pour over peaches in small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Combine coffee cream, vanilla and food coloring.
Let stand, without stirring, while preparing other ingredients.
Stir salt into flour.
Gradually add 1/3 of the cream mixture with whisk or fork as you pour.
Stir in sugar.
Stir in remaining cream.
Let stand for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Line pie pan with unbaked pie crust and sprinkle nutmeg and dot butter on bottom of crust.
Pour in filling.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and continue baking for 45 minutes longer. Shake every 15 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and let come to a boil.
Simmer for one hour or until thick.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown chicken. Put in crock pot. Combine ingredients in small bowl, except peas. Pour over chicken. Cook on low 7-9 hours or cook on high
3-4 hours.
Add peas 1 hour before serving.

title: mexican stuffed mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Place ground beef in 1-quart micro-proof casserole; break up with spoon.
Cook on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Add hot sauce and tomato, blending well.
Fill each mushroom with about 1 teaspoon filling.
Place 10 to 12 mushrooms, stuffing side up, in circle in microwave-proof plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 dozen.
Cooking Time:
5 1/2 to 7 minutes.

title: shake and bake chicken
directions: Mix in order given and store in a tight container.
For chicken, beat up one egg and 3/4 cup milk.
Dip pieces in milk-egg mix, then in Shake 'n Bake.
Can be used on chicken, fish and pork chops.

title: fruit pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until thickened.
Remove from stove and mix with Jell-O and let cool.
Put sliced canned or cooked peaches in baked pie shell and pour mixture over peaches and chill.

title: fat-free carrot-pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups with foil liners.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt into medium bowl.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl at medium speed until soft peaks are formed.
Gradually beat thawed apple juice, increasing mixer speed to high.
Fold milk powder into whites, then fold in wheat or oat bran and flour mixture.
Stir in shredded carrots.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside. Blend margarine, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add alternately the flour, milk and raw zucchini.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts while cake is warm.
Serves 10.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook onion and mushrooms (set aside), then in same skillet, cook meat until light brown.
Reserving 1/3 cup beef broth, stir in remaining broth, catsup, garlic and salt. Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush 1 bag Oreos.
Mix 1 stick butter with 1/2 of Oreos; spread in pan.
Fix 2 boxes of pudding according to directions on box.
Pour over Oreos.
Mix 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip, 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 (8 oz.) cream cheese; spread over 2nd layer.
Mix remaining Oreos with 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip, spread over 3rd layer; chill.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: In pot, dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water; add soup and boil. Add cheese until melted.
Blend in mayo.
Add shrimp, shallots and celery.
Grease mold and fold in mixture.
Chill for at least 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger balls in barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and roll into balls. Place in single layer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Dress a fat 5 or 6 pound chicken.
Cut up and put in large pot.
Cover with water and cook until tender (about 2 1/2 hours). Season to taste.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, artificial sweetener and water in saucepan. Cook over low heat until rhubarb is tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin and Aspartame until dissolved.
Cool slightly; add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: friendship fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Stir well.
Add eggs and stir well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir well and pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip.
I always double the recipe and make 2 pies.
Keep one and give one to a friend.

title: squash pie
directions: In large saucepan, cover the squash with water and boil until well done. Pour the water off. Then pour the water off 2 more times!

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux with flour and oil.
Add garlic; cook until golden brown.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until clear.
Add shrimp, tomatoes and okra; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in water.
Blend well.
Add crab and bay leaves; cook for 30 minutes.
Add oysters and fish; cook 10 minutes.
Let sit before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cook butter, onion and Ro-Tel until done.
Do not brown.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in slow 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Put cheese on top and let melt.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and turkey; drain off fat.
Add chopped garlic, chopped onion and green pepper, broken up canned tomatoes and spaghetti sauce, garlic powder and oregano.
Simmer 45 minutes. Cook lasagna.
Use 7 x 11-inch pan.
Put sauce on bottom, lasagna layer, sauce, 1/2 pound Romano cheese, 1/2 pound cottage cheese, sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers ending up with lasagna on top, with Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: my lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and lemon pie filling.
Mix water and egg yolks.
Add to pie filling.
Put in double boiler and boil-cook slow, stirring often, until bubbly.
Pour into baked pie shells. Beat egg whites for meringue.
Bake at 400° until meringue is light brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan, then line bottom of pan with waxed paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon.
Pour into pan.
Spread dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake 1 hour.
Let cake cool and invert onto plate (pecan layer will then be the bottom crust).

title: bisquick cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mix into a Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Mix well.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1-inch boiling water for 10 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in syrup, ginger and orange peel.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour glaze over carrots.
Stir.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients except marshmallows until thick.
Add marshmallows.

title: cherry coconut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix in bowl the shortening and sugar.
Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla, maraschino cherries and coconut.
Add flour mixture all at once; mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: tortellini delight
directions: Dice the ham and turkey.
Combine the tortellini, broccoli, ham and turkey in a large bowl.
Add the olive oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix.

title: swedish stew
directions: Press the ground beef into the bottom and halfway up the sides of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer each vegetable:
potatoes, onions, carrots and peas.
Spread tomato soup on top.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for three hours.

title: foxy frank appetizers
directions: Simmer in electric frying
pan	on low for 1 hour or in oven at 275° for 2 hours.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add taco mix, tomato sauce, beans and spaghetti.
Cook until spaghetti is done.
Top with grated cheese (Cheddar) and crumbled corn chips.
Serves 6.

title: o'dell's funeral potatoes
directions: Stir together margarine and soup.
Stir in sour cream, cheese and potatoes.
Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 75 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serves 16.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Mash the yolks of hard-cooked eggs, along with can of sardines.
Add a dash of curry powder and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Put the mixture back into the egg whites and garnish with a tiny sprig of parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place whole Waverly crackers in baking dish.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Place chicken over crackers.
Combine soup, sour cream and broth well.
Pour on top of chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mystery pie
directions: Prepare crust using wafers and butter.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 250° for about 1 hour. Sprinkle a few crust crumbs on top before baking.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: nutty white fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Gradually add sugar. Beat in melted chocolate. Add vanilla and salt; mix well. Stir in walnuts. Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill for 4 to 5 hours before cutting. Store in the refrigerator.

title: microwave individual pizzas
directions: Spread each muffin half with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce.
Top each muffin with 3 slices of pepperoni, a few of the mushroom slices and 1 tablespoon of the Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange muffin halves on a paper towel lined plate.
(If desired, sprinkle pizzas with grated Parmesan cheese, chopped onion and chopped black or green olives.)
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until the cheese melts, rotating the plate once during cooking time.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Trim off excess fat from beef.
Cut meat off bone in chunks. Put meat and bone into a 4 to 5-quart heavy metal pan along with 1/2 cup water.
Cover. Cook over medium-high heat until meat releases juices and turns gray, about 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Cook juices away.
Turn meat in rendered fat until well browned on all sides, 30 minutes more.
Lift out meat. Set aside.
To pan, add 1/4 cup water and the vinegar. Scrape pan to loosen browned bits. Add bouillon cubes, chili powder, onions and green pepper.
Cook, stirring for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and their liquid. Break up tomatoes with a spoon. Add kidney beans.
Return meat to pan. Stir to mix. Cover. Simmer until meat is tender enough to fall apart easily, 2 hours.
Discard bone. Skim off fat. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot with cheese, green onion and chips.

title: doritos (taco) salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into small bite size pieces, placing it into a large bowl.
Clean and chop up cucumber, tomato and onion. Add this and drained hamburger meat to lettuce.
Toss this and dressing altogether.

title: dirt cups
directions: Take 2 plastic flower pots (that hold 1 cup) and fill with chocolate pudding.
Top pudding with crushed Oreo mixture.
Stick silk flowers into "dirt".
Place gummy worms around flowers. Serve with a small shovel or spoon.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Heat all ingredients in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Heat 30 more seconds.
Pour over popcorn in bowl.
Mix until coated. Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: rice special
directions: Place rice in a shallow dish.
Mix in soup and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until all liquid has been absorbed.

title: homemade soup
directions: Boil beef until real done.
Remove from broth.
Let cool. Combine rest of ingredients in broth and cook until done.
Pour into a large soup pot; crumble cooled beef and add to vegetables. Add enough water for soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Can be frozen.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine and mix well the oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Drain beans and combine in bowl.
Add chopped green pepper and onion. Pour oil, sugar and vinegar mixture over beans and mix.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Best if marinated for 12 to 24 hours.

title: granola raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Beat eggs in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Stir until milk is dissolved.
Add wheat germ, granola and raisins. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients.
Combine the eggs, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Fry on hot, lightly-greased griddle.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit well, reserving juice from pineapple.
Arrange fruit in a glass baking dish (3-quart size).
Mix cornstarch with fruit juice.
Add melted margarine, cinnamon and brandy.
In a small saucepan, bring to a boil, and cook until thickened; pour over fruit.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: gyro sandwich
directions: Stir together beef, crumbs, onion, 1 tablespoon of the parsley, mint, salt, cinnamon, allspice and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Heat 1/8 cup of oil in a large skillet.
Add meatballs and brown evenly, turning occasionally, until done.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: With hands, rub sugar, paprika, black pepper and salt into cabbage; then add ketchup and vinegar.

title: fruit whip
directions: Sprinkle jello over cheese and let set.
Mix pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.
Add to jello and cheese.
Chill.

title: 5 minute corn relish
directions: Combine corn, celery, onion, vinegar, corn syrup, celery seed, mustard powder and salt in a large bowl until well blended.
Cover tightly and chill until ready to serve.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Add oil, mandarin oranges with juice, eggs and oleo to cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fruit cups
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in Dixie cups.
Freeze.

title: sweet macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted, boiling water; drain, rinse and cool. Add fruit.
Thicken juices with 3/4 cup of sugar, 3 tablespoons of flour and 3 eggs.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Cool and mix with macaroni and fruit.
Let set overnight.

title: french meat pies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg, together.
Brush pie crust with egg.
Pour mixture into 1 pie crust.
Fold second pie crust over mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: deviled crab cakes(deep fry)
directions: Steam onion, green pepper and celery in 1 stick margarine.
Mix with other ingredients, season with salt, 1 teaspoon paprika, 2 teaspoons Old Bay seasoning and a dash of pepper.
Roll into oblong balls.
Roll in flour, dip in beaten egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry 2 to 3 at a time until golden brown.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot heaping full of chopped apples.
(Lid may not fit at start but apples shrink as cooked.)
Drizzle sugar (sweet apples require less sugar), cinnamon, cloves and salt over apples. Cover and cook on High 1 hour.
Lower heat and cook all day until thick and dark in color.
Stir occasionally.
Place in small jars; cool and freeze (leave room for expansion).
Can substitute peaches or pears.
This is so simple to make and so delicious!

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour mixture gradually, beating until well blended.
Add carrots, nuts, coconut, cherries, bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan (grease and flour lightly).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool, wrap and refrigerate for several days.

title: cabbage pockets
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare hot roll mix or make your own raised dough.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Meanwhile, cook meat, salt and pepper; drain off excess fat if necessary.
Add 1 cup finely shredded cabbage and onions.
When dough has doubled; press down and divide into 12 pieces.
Use some flour, or oil, on clean hands and press each piece to about 6 x 7 inches.
Put 1 or 2 tablespoons meat mixture in center area.
Fold sides over meat to seal and then fold end and seal.
Place on greased pan 1-inch apart with sealed side down.
Set aside 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise and lay in a 13 x 9-inch pan cream side up.
Put both puddings in bowl and add 2 cups of milk; beat with mixer until thick.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add last cup of milk and beat.
Spread over Twinkies, then put Cool Whip over top of pudding layer.
Top with nuts. Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large dish place hash brown potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream and onions.
Spread over potatoes.
Top with shredded cheese. Melt oleo; add to cracker crumbs.
Put over other ingredients. Cook, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice salad
directions: To cold, cooked rice, mix the French dressing with the Tabasco sauce.
Let marinate for 1 hour.
Toss in the rest of the ingredients and garnish with parsley.

title: peachy delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry yogurt tarts
directions: In a

small bowl, blend yogurt and 1 cup whipped topping. Spoon the yogurt mixture into the crusts. Arrange 2 halved strawberries around the yogurt on each tart. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Chill 1 hour or until firm. Makes 6 tarts. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until creamy.
Use as a dip for apples, bananas, strawberries, etc.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in baking dish.
Top with crumbs mixed with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed olive cheese log
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except parsley.
Refrigerate until firm (1 to 2 hours).
Shape mixture into a log shape; roll in parsley.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers.
This cheese log is especially nice around Christmastime because of the red and green colors.

title: dream fruit dressing
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise by hand until smooth.
Stir in preserves, lemon juice and curry powder.
Chill until 1 hour before serving.
Stir in Dream Whip and refrigerate until serving time.

title: smiles
directions: Wash apples and cut into quarters. Remove cores and seeds. Cut each quarter section into 4 slices. Spread peanut butter on one side of every slice. Place 3 to 4 marshmallows on one apple slice on peanut butter side. Place another slice on top of Marcello's with peanut butter next to marshmallows. Should look like a mouth with teeth showing.

title: broccoli ham roll-ups
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain.

title: shrimp dip(blazer's; greenwood, sc)
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and let set a few hours before serving.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Thinly slice carrots and celery.
Chop onion and parsley. Slice cabbage and chop into pieces approximately 2-inches long. Saute fresh vegetables in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil until just tender.
Put chicken broth in stockpot.
Add sauteed vegetables. Drain liquid from beans and chickpeas and discard liquid.
Add beans and chickpeas to broth.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with cooked ditalini noodles, Parmesan cheese and fresh rolls.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Make pudding by the directions on the box.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Add milk, butter, salt, remaining sugar, eggs and 3 cups of flour; beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn out onto floured surface.

title: biscotti
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in then knead lightly (dough will be soft).
Divide in half using two small loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden. Remove from pan.
Cut into 1-inch wide slices (diagonally).
Place on sides on cookie sheet and toast lightly on each side for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes in orange sauce
directions: Mix and boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour this sauce over cooked sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
